deck_excerpt: A fun HERO deck that utilizes all the HERO monsters.
deck_description: This is a fun deck that utilizes all the HERO card types, so about 30-40% time, it kinda bricks. Otherwise, the deck follows the traditional HERO playstyle. Play Guide Search out Vision HERO Faris(via Reinforcements/E-Emergency Call to search out Stratos, which can search any HERO monsters upon being summoned) Summon Faris, also while dumping a HERO monster(preferably those with graveyard effects, like shadow mist, liquid soldier, etc.) then place a copy of Vision HERO Increase to the field as a continuous trap, release Faris, then summon Vision HERO Vyon, which then allows you to send a HERO monster to the graveyard(perferably shadow mist or Destiny HERO Malicious)(If you dumped shadow mist(provided that Shadow Mist wasn't used before), search Evil HERO Adusted Gold, then search out Dark Calling) then Banish a HERO from the grave to search polymerization, and link the two Vision HEROs for Xtra HERO Infernal Devicer to reveal Flame Wingman(If necessary, Neos Kluger) to search out Bustnatrix and Avian. Fuse Bustnatrix and Avian for Elemental HERO Sunriser to search out a copy of Miracle fusion If normal summon is still available, summon a HERO monster from hand to link summon Xtra HERO Wonder Driver, then summon a HERO to the bottom center arrow of Wonder Driver to retrieve an fusion/change spell card, and use Wonder Driver and an available HERO monster to go into Xtra HERO Dread Decimator(for this, preferably use Malicious, or an atm useless fusion monster). And then summon either Flame Wingman, or one of the omni HEROs(Escuridao or Absolute Zero). Next turn If Neos Fusion isn't available, go into the 2nd copy of Xtra HERO Infernal Devicer to search out Neos and Yubel to summon Neos Kluger, and attack for game with the HEROs.

deck_excerpt: search prioritize spells, and spam draw for exodia (it can FTK given right setup)
deck_description:
1. use toon table to search all toon tables before searching toon red eyes
  2. use magician of prophecy when summoned to search secrets, then use secrets to search knowledge unless you have one in hand, then search a magician of prophecy
  3. use allure of darkness with toon red eyes
  4. use cursed bamboo swords on your numerons because they are destroyed during end phase, and it will let you search golden or flaming
  5. if you can, ALWAYS use memories of hope before summoning zexal or sunya, it will maximize the cards you get
  6. needless to say, use one day of peace and upstart whenever you get the chance

The main idea is to mill a bunch of cards then rekindling and watch things go crazy  I added a little salamangreat for utility, I'm not entirely sure if it'll work  De-synchro is really good at times  Use hyper librarian to get more rekindlings and make big plays  Accesscode to swing for game  Did I forget to mention that lavalval dragun is a really good de-synchro target?  The main flaw is that you can walk yourself into a corner sometimes.  Overall a fun deck, I hope you enjoy it!

deck_excerpt: TCGs exclusive are good!  edit : i meant fun :^)
deck_description: hi, it's the worst guy again :D  Today is a vendread deck, without the zombie strat cuz it's not about winning it's about loosing with style. we all know that.  So the strat is simple sending your zombie monster to the GY with the Uni-zombie and the Samurai skull. you can also get rid of cards in your opp hand with Hand destruction while you can send your dead zombie card to the GY. Mezuki cuz we need to summon back either our rituals (once they have already been ritual summoned) or some folder to link on your Vampire sucker or Cross-sheep. We only use the 3 revenant and 3 houndhorde sinc they give the effect to banish monster or Spell/traps which is really good atm. Pre-preparation of rites due to the deck being a ritual based deck, but we can only get Revendread origin and Revendread slayer to our hand, but it's good enought combo to make the deck run quite well. The deck have lots of weaness, can't really play throught 2 handtraps or even 1 with a bad hand, but most of the time it's full combo. with 2 ritual monster on the board+ a link 2, you can even add an I:P masquerena so you can go for an apolousa during your opponent turn.  And.. that's it. not a lot to say it's a TCG exclusive deck with good artwork, good lore and mechanics but lacks a good engine and the endboard is not that sufficient nowadays but it's good enought for casual player, pretty cheap, exept for hand traps but you can easily go for sets of forbidden lances chalice and robe so no worries :)

So you want an alternative option to buy three structure decks and mash them? Something not too hard to learn and no long combos to memorize? Well, I've got just what you need....  Paleo frog has been around in various forms for the past four or so years as a rogue strategy that always shows up in bigger tournaments. The deck revolves around traps and interrupting your opponent's lines of play. I feel this is the best way for a new player to learn the game as the more you play against different decks, the more you learn to counteract them. With combo decks you just focus on what you want to do.  This is a budget version of the deck so sadly you only get two copies of toadally awesome. Getting a third copy will be top priority as well as three copies of trap trick. Luckily, you can get those cards for perhaps 5 or 6 dollars more total. As it stands this will certainly hold you for a while at a locals level.

deck_name: The Legendary Fisherman of White Sea
deck_excerpt: This is a deck skeleton for a Legendary Fisherman/Water Synchro build that uses Fisherman's and different Water engines, purely for research/brainstor
deck_description: This is mainly a small "fun" build revolved around the Fisherman's and the White Aura's with the main focus of building up the GY and searching the Deck to spam a bit and make Synchro plays. That being said, the Legendary Fisherman III is more like a "bank shot" and only comes out occasionally, its more often a Tatsunoko or Moray of Greed target when its around too early in the hand.  The build isn't 100% perfect. I'm pretty sure there are some better cards to employ than some of these. If anything, its meant to be a skeleton as you can add and remove cards as you please according to you and also give yourself ideas on how to make a Fisherman Water deck playable.  I am aware there is a better way to play Fisherman with cards such as the Combat Star cards, but meh, often has felt weird to me playing them like that and it not being a true Water deck like intended for the monster and being true to Mako Tsunami. But I also wouldn't mind hearing ideas for Legendary Fisherman and seeing what kind of deck you can build around it whether Water or not.  Main idea is simple enough regarding combos, one combo only requires you needing a Megalo and Deep Sea Diva in hand.  >NS Diva >Activate Diva effect, SS Neptabyss >Activate Neptabyss effect, send Dragoon to  GY, add a 2nd Dragoon to hand >Activate Dragoon effect in GY, add a 2nd Neptabyss to hand >Activate Megalo, discard Nebtabyss and Dragoon, SS Megalo >Activate both the 2nd Neptabyss's and 2nd Dragoon's effect, Neptabyss will SS a Dragoon from GY while the Dragoon you discarded with Megalo will add another Megalo to hand or something else if already have a Level 7 in hand. >Link off Diva and Megalo for Needlefiber >Activate Needlefiber effect, SS another Diva >Synchro Summon Tatsunoko with 2nd Diva and Neptabyss >Synchro Summon Bihamut with Tatsunoko and Level 7 in hand (Probably Megalo if you added him to hand earlier) >Activate Bihamut effect, SS Token >Link off Needlefiber, the Token, and Dragoon for a Apollousa (3 negates) Then opponent's turn, SS another Token with Bihamut.

Inspired by Alex Cimo's Progression Series on Youtube, I decided I'd attempt to reteach some of my friends how to play the TCG; however, most of them have never experienced anything passed the GX era. We'll start by opening 1 Booster Box (24 packs) of the first five packs released during the 5Ds era: from The Duelist Genesis to Ancient Prophecy. I was very fortunate to open a good pool of the Blackwing cards and some versitial Synchro monsters with Red Dragon Archfiend as my deck's current ace. I also pulled some of the Assault mode cards including Red Dragon Archfiend/Assualt Mode so having that in the side could come in handy. For spell and trap removal I'll have to rely on Power Tool Dragon (to search Double Tool or Silver Wing) and Release Restraint. Initialy my strategy was to use Fane the Steel Chain's effect to deal damage through piercing with Bora the Spear or Armed Wing; however, as a level 2 non-tuner, it doesn't fit the roll of synchro material with what I have available: Gishilnodon requires a level 3 non-tuner which means I'll most likely use Blizzard to bring back a Kalut from grave to summon it and without a level 1 Blackwing tuner, I wouldn't be able to use a level 3 and Fane to summon Armed Wing. However, Blizzard + Kalut and Fane can make level 7 synchros or Gale + Kalut and Fane could make Red Dragon Archfiend, but that requires a little more setup. For now, Fane will be in the side deck along with my Assault Mode support, 3 copies of Fake Feather, and 2 copies of Gozen Match. The Arcanite Magician wouldn't be usable but because I have some Assault Mode support I thought I'd include it in the extra deck.

deck_excerpt: Extra Deck destruction is really what it is
deck_description: The goal of the deck is really just to slowly chip away at your opponent's Extra Deck. You should be going first and by the time it is your opponent's turn, you will have about 2 to 4 cards ripped out of your opponent's Extra Deck but usually 2. 2 of which would be your choice. A Deskbot engine and a Lefty/Righty Driver engine help turbo out Dogmatika Albaz Knight with Herald of the Arc Light. 2 Dogmatika Albaz Knight which rips 1 card of your choice from your opponent's ED every turn and is Punishment on legs since you can send N'tss from yours. 2 Ashiyan for recycling. 3 Fleurdelis for Extra Deck negation. 3 Ecclesia since she searches a lot of the deck. 1 Maximus which can take out 2 card from your opponent's ED and it can also help set up your Albaz Knight plays. Deskbot and Lefty/Righty Driver engines. 1 DMOC as the target for Chaos Scepter Blast. And 3 Ash. 3 Nadir Servant for searching. 3 Dogmatikas which is your ritual spell (and basically Nadir Servant). 3 Chaos Scepter Blast which is nontargeting banishing of any card on the field face-down and it is always live since you will always have a lv8 spellcaster on field. 3 Pot of Prosperity. 1 Encounter. 3 Punishment. deck_name: 8-Axis Abhyss ft. NEW SPELL - Combo Tutorial
deck_excerpt: I think overall this deck is very solid and is a good rogue tier OTK deck at best. It won’t top any tournaments or anything like that, but it is a fun
deck_description: Welcome to my updated Abhyss list!! The new spell just dropped and it is really good. It is basically a foolish burial for any reptile and can also serve as a monster reborn if you have 5 or more reptiles in the GY. Getting the reptiles in the graveyard is fairly easy using snake rain, aka the painful choice of the deck. The new spell can also be searched VERY easily and can be used to summon the big level 8 Abhyss monsters from the GY without having to tribute monsters!! I am playing a level 8 (and kind of level 4) focused deck since all the abhyss monsters are either level 4 or 8. This deck is more focused on level 8’s than 4’s. For level 8 support (8-axis) we are playing 3 danger! Bigfoot!, 3 danger! Thunderbird!, 3 trade-in (staple), 3 alpha, 3 sea turtle kaiju, 3 sticky string kaiju and all of the level 8 abhyss monsters. This is a going 2nd OTK based deck purely focused on breaking boards and killing the opponent. Going 2nd you can use the various removal cards you have to break boards, the kaiju slumbers, all 6 kaijus, alpha (synergises well with kaijus since it can bounce a kaiju the opponent has back to your hand and then you can summon the kaiju back to your opponent’s field by tributing something else and alpha can bring itself back to the field as a rank 8 xyz target), bigfoot and thunderbird (have removal effects when discarded). Then your goal is to get 2 level 8 monsters on to your field and go into Number 97: Dragublion. Then you can use its effect to summon numeron dragon from the extra deck and you can otk using it since it will have 9000 attack after you use it’s effect. It’s attack will be 13000 if you have a rank 4 on the field as well (very likely) and that can hit over any monster the opponent controls with 5000 or less attack (I highly doubt they will have anything with that much attack so it is pretty much a win). If they put their monsters in defense - SLAP A KAIJU ON THEM!! The deck is not dead going 1st either. The plan going 1st is to set up your deity of the abhyss, a dweller and a hope harbinger (best case scenario) or the board can even be as simple as a Bagooska pass.    I think overall this deck is very solid and is a good rogue tier OTK deck at best. It won’t top any tournaments or anything like that, but it is a fun deck to mess around with and also allows you to take a break from the meta and have some fun!! To me personally it is amazing to have a break from the meta, I post mostly meta decks but building and testing this deck for a change was very enjoyable indeed.    If you are interested, I do an in depth deck profile and combo tutorial in my youtube channel, I recommend watching it since it can help you understand what I actually said on here and you will get a basic understanding of how the deck is played.    Link - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=aF1sTi69cQE   Also make sure to answer the poll question down below!! Today’s question is: What is your favorite anime themed deck?   Thanks, and I’ll see you next time!! :D

deck_excerpt: The deck is very strong overall and is definitely a tier 1 contender in the current metagame. The amazement cards do not change how the deck is played
deck_description:
Hello all and welcome to my Amazing Zoodiac Eldlich build!! The deck is Amazing because it uses some cards from the Amazement archetype (LIOV). They synergie very well with this deck because of how many traps the deck plays. Amazement is also an archetype revolving around traps and combined with eldlich they are Amazing!!   Before we do the deck explanation, just a quick reminder that the deck explanation, All the combos and explanations on ways to best use your resources are ALL on my Youtube video. Subscribing to the channel would be a great way to support me and the channel!   Link to the video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ESRWceGnH4o   BANLIST NOTICE (IMPORTANT)   If something in this deck were to get hit on the March 2021 banlist (very unlikely), it will not be something major. The worst thing that can possibly happen would be a sanguine semi limit or a eldland semi limit or a tenki limit. NONE OF THESE DO ANYTHING TO THIS DECK. If something were to happen, I’ll make sure to update the list after the banlist with the minor changes. If tenki were to get hit (unlikely - did not even get hit in the zoo format) - just play more zoo bodies. If sanguine gets hit, just play an extra white or black elixdir (depends on play style) and if eldland were to get hit, just play how many ever copies of it as possible and fill up space in the main deck with handtraps. I will update the deck when the banlist drops so do not fret.    Why administrator is OP (In this deck) -    The deck is not running the entire amazement package. It is running the absolute minimum to keep this deck in the meta tier. This is better than the basic zoo eldlich build because this can put up more interruptions. For the amazement cards we are playing 3 Amazement Administrator and 3 of the amazement attraction horror house (the one with the book of moon effect) and that is all. Administrator is OP because of how much it can disrupt the opponent, break boards and generate advantage. Yes, that 1 card can do all of that. Administrator can special summon itself when a trap is activated. Then, it can equip the attraction trap from the deck onto an opponent's monster to flip it face down. Now since the monster is facedown, the equip card goes to the GY (equip cards go to the GY if the target it is equipped to leaves the field or is flipped face down) so the trap will be in the GY. Then you can banish the trap from the grave to destroy a card on the field! It is any card on the field, monster or back row, face up or face down!! On top of all of that you have a monster on the field to link off into (depending on your situation) one of the knightmares or even Black luster Soldier!! When you draw it with imperm or if your opponent plays any kind of trap that can activate itself turn 1, making it a VERY high impact handtrap. It can also use it’s removal effect during your turn and be liked for more devastation. When you go first, since the deck has so many traps, it just adds up to your negates and makes it easier to OTK next turn with the removal and since it can be linked. This card literally brings the whole package.    Deck Ratios -  
Amazement! Cards 
  • 3 administrator 
  • 3 attraction horror house (the one with the book of moon effect)
 For the amazement cards we are playing 3 Amazement Administrator and 3 of the amazement attraction trap card and that is all. The trap negates an opponent’s monster’s effect or flips a monster the opponent controls face down based on which monster it is equipped to. The monster (administrator) can summon itself when a trap is activated (when either player activates a trap) as a quick effect (can be done on opponent’s turn) and it can also equip a monster on the field with an attraction trap (quick effect). This makes it a handtrap essentially and can also cause more damage next turn by banishing the attraction trap you equipped from the graveyard to use administrators’ removal effect (assuming the monster you equipped the card to left the field). The trap (if drawn without the monster) is not a brick because it is basically a book of moon and can simply be set like any other trap. You can also resolve administrator constantly going 1st and second for an high impact negate. If the opponent is playing some kind of trap based deck that administrator can come in clutch. 
Zoodiac Cards
  • 3 ramram
  • 2 whiptail
  • 3 tenki
  • 1 barrage 
 I am playing 3 Ramram (2000 defense and protects you against dangerous traps) and 2 Whiptail (can attach itself and has the removal effect that banishes) for the monsters. 5 is more than enough and there are plenty of ways to search these. For spells I am playing 3 Tenki (can search any zoo) and 1 barrage (can pop itself to special a zoo from the deck). In total that is 9 cards to search zoo monsters and that is ≈ ¼ of the deck. You should expect a zoo monster in hand in about 1 in 4 cards which is the ideal ratio. Tenki is really good with eldlich since it is a continuous spell. It can be sent to the GY to bring back golden boy with 3500 attack. 
Eldlich Ratios
  • 2 golden lord
  • 3 eldland
  • 3 sanguine
  • 3 Haquero
  • 3 conquistador
 I am playing 2 Golden lord for the monsters (Obviously the only eldlich monster). For Spells I am playing 3 Eldland (only good eldlich spell). For traps I am playing 3 sanguine (the best elixdir trap), 3 Haquero (can banish from the GY) and 3 Conquistador (can pop). This is just the standard eldlich ratio, no explanation needed there. 
Non archetypical Traps
  • 3 Imperm
  • 3 solemn strike
  • 2 Dinomischus
 By this I mean traps that do not go with eldlich or amazement. For this I am playing 3 Imperm (is a handtrap as well), 3 solemn strike (high impact negation, is also a counter trap) and 2 Dinomischus (great removal and can bring itself back from the GY to use as link material). All of these are to set and interrupt the opponent. 
Handtraps
  • 3 ash
  • 3 imperm
  • 3 administrator (in some cases)
 I am playing 3 ash (counter literally anything) and 3 imperm (is not only a real trap but a handtrap as well). Yes I know I included imperm in both categories. Imperm is a good option because if you activate it, it lets you bring out administrator turn 1 (opponent’s turn) and you can equip the attraction trap using administrator to an opponent’s monster later in the turn for a high impact disruption!! (Book of moon during opponent’s first turn)
Bricks
  • none
 BRICKLESS LETS GOOOOOOO
  The extra deck -   The extra deck is just 2 of every zoodiac monster (except drident which is limited) and 2 zeus for the xyz (zoodiac) package. For the links you have Knightmare Phoenix (pops backrow), Knightmare Unicorn (shuffles), Black Luster Soldier (OTK) and Barricageborg Blocker (recycle). Notice all the link monsters do not list effect monsters as materials so you can link the golden land traps into them as well.    Conclusion -   The deck is very strong overall and is definitely a tier 1 contender in the current metagame. The amazement cards do not change how the deck is played, it is just an extra mechanic that the deck uses to make it more powerful. Amazement makes this deck better in a number of ways and that is why this deck is Amazing!   Remember that the deck explanation, All the combos and explanations on ways to best use your resources are ALL on my Youtube video. Subscribing to the channel would be a great way to support me and the channel!   Link to the video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ESRWceGnH4o   Also make sure to answer today’s poll down below!! Today’s question is: What is your favorite staple and why?   Thanks, and I’ll see you next time!! :D

hi
Focuses on the ease that Weather Painters have to clear the field with their banishing effects by running a lot of board wiping options in Dark Hole, Torrential Tribute and Raigeki.  by Jepeseta.

Main combo can start with either Null or Nihil + one normal summon, ideally Null and Zoha. End board can be Draglubion + N100/Nc107 and a boss monster of your choice (usually Ogdoabyss) but I tried to give more options in the extra deck. Lair of Darkness is always good to have on hand (unless it's turn 1) to help facilitate combos easier.  This is my first attempt at making something even remotely competitive (probably rogue at best, though), so I'm open to critiques

deck_excerpt: Atlandis une fuerzas con los Drytron y Saturn para traer la destrucción inminente! Diezma a tu oponente! OwO Atlandis joins forces with the Drytron a
deck_description:
Deck creado por: Darklab Objetivo: Acabar con la vida del oponente usando a Chronomaly Atlandis y Agent Saturn OwO. Link a la demostración del Deck: >>>>>https://youtu.be/4Df67balYJc<<<<< Requisitos para iniciar el combo: Para iniciar el combo necesitamos tener en mano a Drytron Alpha, Drytron Zeta y Cyber Angel Benten (o uno de los "ladrillos") Searchers para buscar los requisitos:
  • Where Arf Thou: Sirve para añadir un Drytron cuando ya hay uno en el campo. Ya que el uso de Alpha y Zeta es intercambiable, sirve para buscar a cualquiera de los dos.
  • Jack in the Hand: Debe ser usado primero por ser algo impredecible. Usualmente escogeremos a Alpha, Zeta y Gamma. Si el oponente toma a Alpha o Zeta, escogemos al otro. Si toma a Gamma, no hay problema, ya que llevamos otra copia, y además escogemos al Drytron que necesitamos.
  • Cyber Emergency: Literalmente trae a la mano cualquier Drytron.
  • Foolish Burial: Cuando hablamos de Drytron, el cementerio y la mano son casi lo mismo.
  • Drytron Nova: Trae a cualquier Drytron al campo, el cual puedes enviar al cemenerio al usarlo para invocar a Linkuriboh.
  • Drytron Fafnir: Añade a Nova a la mano.
  • Preparation of Rites: Sirve para traer a Benten a la mano.
  • Ritual Sanctuary: Trae a Benten a coste de descartar una magia, que en este deck, hay de sobra.
  • Terraforming: Es el más versátil, ya que puede traer a Fafnir (si necesitas un Drytron) o a Ritual Sanctuary (si necesitas a Benten).
Ladrillos:
  • The Agent of Judgement - Saturn: Con él rematamos al oponente, además que al invocarse, activa el efecto de Benten.
  • Soul of Purity and Light: Con ella tendremos los materiales necesarios para invocar a Chronomaly Atlandis.
  • Zeradias, Herald of Heaven: Descartándolo, tendremos The Sanctuary in the Sky.
  • The Sanctuary in the Sky: Es necesario para resolver el efecto de Agent Saturn.
Pros:
  • Deck bastante consistente.
  • No tiene garnets, y el único ladrillo verdadero es Drytron Meteornis, por lo que todo es útil.
  • Puede baitear Impermanence y Veiler en Mu-Beta Fafnir si tienes un buscador extra para Gamma.
  • Puede baitear hantraps tempranas con los extenders suficientes.
  • Versátil. Es fácil de añadir los requisitos al estar el Deck lleno de buscadores.
  • Si todo falla, con los cuerpos en campo se puede hacer invocaciones Link poderosas (como Masquerena->Kurnugias en turno del oponente), ya que el combo no usa todo el extra deck
Contras:
  • A pesar de ser consistente, puede que toque puro Drytron o puro Benten/ladrillo, en cuyo caso es gg.
  • El deck depende de que tú y el oponente tengan los mismos LP al inicio. Si el oponente consigue aumentar sus LP o quemar la tuya, el combo no funcionará.
  • El deck es susceptible a Nibiru, Called by the grave y Ghost Belle, al igual que a Veiler e Impermanence si los usan correctamente.
  • La prioridad para traer a los ladrillos es muy importante. Siempre es Saturn > Soul of Purity > Zeradias. Saturn no puede ser el último, ya que su invocación activa un Benten, si nos olvidamos de él, es gg. Soul of Purity es necesario para traer a Atlandis, el cual se activa antes que Saturn, y aunque es posible invocar a Saturn antes que a Atlandis, no es así si hemos baiteado un Veiler con Mu-Beta Fafnir. Zeradias sólo es necesario al final de todo, por lo que no es tan importante para realizar los combos.

deck_excerpt: Defence is the best offence... Ecept when it's not
deck_description: It's a meme deck, probs won't work IRL.

So, I decided to borrow the idea of MBT's moron banlist and decided that I would make one that I believe would fix a good chunk of the problems with YuGiOh at the moment Update 3/19/21: I have made a few changes, for one limited cards in the main deck are marked by one for one and unlimited cards are marked by TTT, neither of these cards are on the list itself, but are there as organizational tools Update 3/21: cutting droll off, and adding a few more unbans

Banned:

Monsters:

Miscellaneousaurus, This just deletes all interaction when you play against dinos Crystron Halqifibrax, I believe that if a card gets more cards banned because of it, then it's the real problem card and should go Predaplant Verte Anaconda, This limits the design of fusion spells and monsters going forward and I don't like that, I also want rainbow neos turbo to be fun again. Guardragon Elpy, dragons are too good and this card is busted and needs to go

Spells:

Mystic Mine - This card is one of the most degenerate cards in the game, it just deletes all fun and interaction from the game The Phantom Knights' Rank-Up-Magic Launch, This limits the designs of DARK XYZ monster going forward and it just kinda shouldn't have been unbanned in the first place

Traps:

Skill drain - This card is just kind of broken due to it basically making it required to have an out in the for of backrow to stop (if a floodgate can't be outed by Phoenix, it shouldn't be in the game) The Monarchs erupt - same reasons as Skill drain, but in some cases just better

Limited (or to one):

Monsters:

Blaster, Dragon Ruler of Infernos - this card isn't all that good, it's one of the worst dragon rulers and having it at one will probably just be a cool thing for volcanics Destrudo, the Lost Dragon's Frisson - Honestly, this card got banned for no reason, yes it makes halq, but so does basically every single deck right now, I just want to make dawn dragster in BA again Astrograph Sorcerer, Pend isn't good and this card won't change it Performapal Skullcrobat Joker, Pend is still not good Orcust Harp Horror - orcust is garbage, at this point nothing less than a mermaid unban would really matter Lunalight Tiger, most of the degenerate stuff this card has enabled has been hit in some way Thunder Dragon Colossus - This card also was banned for no reason, putting it to one would do nothing Elder Entity Norden - instant fusion is limited, this card can come back Salamangreat Miragestallio, Salad is garbage and this card won't change much Saryuja Skull Dread, this is to check deep-draw decks Denglong, First of the Yang Zing, this is a good card, but I don't think it's good enough today to see any play.

Spells:

Quick Launch, E-tele is at one and this card is better than E-tele 90% of the time (it isn't even OPT) Heavy Storm - Feather duster is just better than this card, having more backrow removal wouldn't hurt anyone Change of heart - this card would just be a decently strong turn 2 card, I don't think it would be all that bad Fossil dig - Dinos don't need better ROTA Invocation, I like invokeds, but it is getting kinda stale Magical Meltdown, See the card above Nadir Servant, This is a hit to dogma because that could get out of hand fast That Grass Looks Greener, I just think this would be funny

Traps:

Ultimate offering - it's probably too slow to really matter, and I think it would be funny There Can Be Only One - another degenerate floodgate, it's not the worst so I'll only limit it Eldlixir of Scarlet Sanguine, eld is kinda boring these days, so a slap on the wrist would be good

Off The List:

Monsters:

Master Peace, the true dracoslaying king - this card is just bad now, it wouldn't see much play and it's way too easy to out Dinowrestler Pankratops - This is just a cool going second card that was limited for no real reason Red-Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon, I think enough damage to dragons has been done for this to come off True King Lithosagym, the Disaster, Dinos got hit hard too, so I'll throw them a bone Infernity Archfiend, This card is not a problem Dinomight Knight, the true dracofighter - Draco is bad, this would do nothing Double iris magician - for as much as we meme about PEND BEST DECK LET'S GOOOOO, it's pretty bad in all honesty Yata Garasu - this card is just bad now, the yata lock is near impossible to pull off now All the tuners banned because of Halq, Noodl is gone so these can come back Night Assailant, This card is too slow to matter nowadays the jars, these are too slow to matter now Speedroid Terrortop, this is a bit suspect, but I do think this could come back, I can only really see this be used to either insulate combos from nibiru, or to make cherubini. If you can show me a combo that breaks this card, I will not have it on here. Tellarknight Ptolemaeus - isn't good any more, turn one CDI isn't as broken as it used to be Trishula, Dragon of the Ice Barrier, This card isn't a problem Daigusto Emeral, this card has seem little to no play

Spells :

Raigeki - evenly is a three so why can't this be Reasoning - won't do much but make infernoids more funny Called by the grave - This card's limit was a mistake, it can come back Dimensional fissure - this is fine really, I don't think it will be a big deal Symbol of heritage - it's a more situational living fossil A hero lives, Heroes aren't good Draco Face-Off, This would do nothing Sekka's light, This card promotes an interesting play style I want to see again Mind control, This card has no real reason to be limited, going second is still bad Trickstar Light Stage, This was limited because of orcust, it can come back now Gold Sarcophagus, This won't do much, thunder won't be too crazy Chain Strike, Chain burn has been dead for a long time Slash Draw, Skull Dread is at one so this doesn't do anything anymore Card destruction, it's a -1 that has no real use today

Traps:

Macro Cosmos - like DiFi this could come back no problem Red Reboot, this stops trap decks and does nothing else Wall of revealing light, Battle traps are bad and last turn doesn't exist anymore Time Seal - this card is just awful, it won't see any play     If you think I'm wrong then send me a decklist proving it, also I didn't have the space for firewall, but we all know that's coming off.

deck_excerpt: A somewhat unique deck that makes use of the Magician of Faith and Needle Worm together to mill your opponent's cards :)
deck_description: Okay first off: yes, I'm writing this in Comic Sans ^^ This deck is an odd one in my opinion. As far as I'm aware, there are no Magician of Faith / Needle Worm decks out there in the same sense as this deck. The aim of this deck is to make your opponent draw out. Easy, right? It may seem unconventional and does require some patience, however I can assure you that this deck is more than capable of putting up a fight against some tougher decks.  Let's talk strategy. There are 2 main parts to this deck: the mill power, and the protect/prevent part (PPP :P) PPP - I was hesitant to include it at first, but Mystic Mine will be your main form of protection in this deck. I know how frustrating it can be to less experienced players, which is why I was on and off about the idea, however, I finally gave in; sorry Swords of Revealing Light, you just won't cut it. To back up the Mystic Mine we have Field Barrier. This protects the mine from being destroyed by opponents, but also by it's own effect. Get both on the field and you're pretty much set - just make sure to play MM BEFORE FB. This deck also features the classic Battle Fader. You could exchange it for Swift Scarecrow which would probably be better, but I prefer Battle Fader :) I have also included 3 copies of Threatening Roar. I think this card works perfectly for this deck. It can stop attacks, but due to it's nature, it can also be used to allow only a few attacks through. This means that you can let your opponent clear your board a little to make way for new monsters, while also reaping the benefits of their effect and then preventing any further assault, should you find yourself in a situation without Mystic Mine's effect. Now for the mill power - there is of course the Needle Worm, which is better for situations where you need to mill your opponent quickly before it's too late. Make use of the Book of Moon/Taiyou to gain the worm's effect more than once per turn, leaving devastating amounts of your opponent's deck strewn to the grave. However there is one more little loop if you will in this deck. It is a simple, 2-card combo that works really well in my opinion, the Magician of Faith and Book of Eclipse (Bare in mind this only works if your opponent controls at least 1 non-link monster). Basically, you'll have a magician on the field. Activate the book and flip all monsters face-down. At the end of the turn, your opponent's will be flipped up, and they'll draw a card for each. For maximum gain from this little combo, activate the book as your opponent enters their battle phase; it'll prevent them from attacking :) (Chain to their End Phase if they skip battle). Then, during your turn, flip your magician, recover the book and repeat. By having other magicians or worms on the field as well as this, you'll also be able to trigger their effects every turn, essentially allowing you to reuse spells and mill your opponent's deck indefinitely. This comes in handy for cards like The Shallow grave, where you can constantly reuse them, giving your opponent more and more monsters to fuel your combo. Cup of Ace in this deck is a win-win card. If you flip heads, you get 2 cards closer to fulfilling your combo. If tails, well your opponent has another 2 cards shaved from their deck Other cards in the deck are mainly draw power to help get the cards you need. The extra deck is mainly fodder for Extravagance, and can consist of any cards you wish, but the cards I've listed can come in handy in particular situations. I would like to note that the underrated card Clara and Rushka, the Ventriloduo is also included. If you don't fancy suiciding your Sangan or WotBF, then this link monster can also do the trick. Unfortunately, it can only be summoned during MP2, although this deck doesn't require any attacking anyways, so it works out pretty well, and it can easily be taken off the board with a Phoenix or Cerberus. What else.. Metaverse is self-explanatory, and so is Ojama Trio (give your opponent more monsters to fulfil Mystic Mine's conditions) Something I would like to mention when it comes to playing this deck is this: DO NOT BE AFRAID TO PASS THE TURN! Sometimes it is better to just wait for cards to be drawn rather than playing every single move possible. One thing I've found is that it is very easy to find yourself with an abundance of Threatening Roars and Battle Faders, so even if you haven't got the mine, you'll always have a backup :) Potential weaknesses to this deck that I've found are archetypes such as Kaijus and Monarchs that are able to tribute your monsters. Unfortunately, I have not found a way around this yet, but I'll be sure to update if and when I do. I also saw a guy who was running Monarchs and had a trap that would put spells/traps from their grave back into the deck, which allowed them to stall to victory. This is my first upload on here and I hope that someone will find a good laugh in my quirky little creation here. Good luck duelists! Feel free to contact my Discord to discuss this or any of my future decks with me, or even just brag about a sweet win you got with it - Katsuki#8104 :)

deck_excerpt: Rogue control deck that can keep up with meta decks
deck_description:
Overview Since the banlist hit of Dinowrestler Pankratops and Red Reboot, I've started to explore rogue control decks that can keep up with meta decks, in the end the deck that I think that fits in those category is Altergeist. This archetype is really good at disrupting your opponent while gaining more resources, it can also fit in handtraps without losing it's consistency, which is important in the current meta due to the fast paced playstyle of decks nowadays. Like what people says, "The deck is only as good as its user" this deck certainly lives up to that phrase, it's deadly when it's in the hand of a person who knows how to utilize it. As a control deck you need to study the decks that will be used by your fellow duelists, knowing which card to disrupt is the key factor for you to achieve victory. Deck Component Explanation Altergeist Cards - A standard ratio of altergeist cards. I think most of the altergeist decks have the same ratio as this one because adding or subtracting of these cards will lower it's consistency. Handtraps - Handtraps are important in this fast paced meta, allowing your opponent to complete their combo without disruption is like asking to lose.
  • Ash Blossom is a must have since it can stop adding cards to the hand.
  • The PSY-Frame bundle is my second favorite handtrap in this deck since it can disrupt your opponent and at the same time it can protect you from your opponent's handtraps.
  • The last but not the least is my favorite handtrap in this deck, Infinite Impermanence, it synergize well with altergeist because you can trigger multifaker after you activate it.
Solemns - At first I was planning to put 3 judgment, but after I analyzed the meta, putting striker would be a good idea and since we have Imperial Order, it can make up for the other judgment. Imperial Order - It's a good card in this control deck since this deck doesn't have many spell cards. Extenders -
  • One for one is a must in an altergeist deck because it's an additional meluseek.
  • Running one Three Tactical Talents is a good idea since it's versatile, you can use it's draw 2 if your extravagance or meluseek has been negated by ash blossom, or you can use it's take control effect to steal one of your opponent's monster.
Pot of Extravagance - Your one and only draw power card (not considering Three Tactical Talents). You can use this a bait for your opponent's handtrap to chain psy-frame gamma. Forbidden Droplets - Just in case you lose the dice roll, you can use this to break your opponent's board that takes them 10 minutes to make, only to be destroyed by a control deck. Extra Deck - The extra deck cards are pretty handy depending on the situation.
  • PSY-Framelord Omega - After you successfully resolve psy-framegear gamma, synchro summon this card to do it's thing.
  • Borrelsword Dragon - In some cases that you need to finish the game fast because you feel the you can't control the game if it goes longer, have no worry as you have this card. Just pray that it doesn't get banish by pot of extravagance.
  • Accesscode Talker - BOARD WIPE!!!!
  • Knightmare Unicorn - If there is a card that limits your movement on the field, return it to the deck using this card.
  • Primabanshee - Can be used to summon multifaker.
  • Selene - An easier way to get your link 4 monsters
  • Knightmare Phoenix - Same as knightmare unicorn but replace "return it to the deck" with "destroy"
  • Hexstia - Your favorite extra deck monster. Use this card against monsters that is not affected by card effects and has a big attack. Negate the spell/trap of your opponent. And add an alteregist card from your deck to your hand
  • Linkuriboh - To trigger meluseek effects and to waste your opponent's attack.
  • Almiraj - To trigger meluseek and silquitous.
  • Anima - To trigger meluseek and equip your opponent's monster to this.
Side Deck -
  • Nibiru - THE ROCK!!!!!! To stop combo decks.
  • HFD - Sweep your opponent's backrow.
  • DRNM - Part of the 2 card deadly combo.
  • Cosmic Cyclone - To get rid of your opponent's backrow. It's more effective against eldlich
  • Evenly Matched - Part of the 2 card deadly combo.
  • Summon Limit - Effective to completely control swarm decks.
  • Imperial Iron Wall - Effective against banish decks and ELDLICH
Budget Friendly Alternatives Three Tactical Talents - Book of Moon, It can bait your opponent's negates and can be use to disrupt their combo. Pot of Extravagance - Pot of Duality, It is what it is. Forbidden Droplets - Water Kaiju and Wind Kaiju, the downside of using this is you're gonna have a hard time against drytrons. Accesscode Talker - Mekk-Knight Crusadia Avramax, Instead of a board wipe, you can just summon this card as a boss card. Reminders
  • As a control deck it's important to study other decks in order to know when is the right time to disrupt them.
  • Do not rush to end the game quickly (unless you cannot control your opponent any longer), remember you're using a control deck.
  • Know how to play around when most of your extra deck cards are banished.
  • After you activate altergeist manifestation, you can chain personal spoofing to return altergeist manifestation to your deck, in that way you can special summon an altergeist monster in your gy without the trap card being sent to the gy.

deck_excerpt: One hit instant death with guide! big monster alert!!!
deck_description: If you don't know what clock is then I'll tell you, it's a small cyberse "archetype" that uses the card cynet fusion. I found out recently about how broken the link 2 clock lizard is.   So I’ve played a few matches, this deck is a going second consistent OTK deck that can play through about three negates (unless one is a nibru) before crumbling apart from my experience so far. I’ve been cleaning players clocks (pun totally intended) with one attack. You may argue with some of my choices but I believe that every card in the deck works the way I want it to but I’ll still be open for advice for things to add.   In the guide below I’ll explain the list, why I picked the cards, and the combos   List:   3 clock wyvern (an absolutely necessary 3 of in this deck, you have 9 cards in the deck that’ll open it for you)   1 RAM clouder (summons a cyberse from the grave, you can replace it with something like swap cleric)   3 ROM cloudia (mainly for backup and converter, latency comes up, but rarely)   3 lady debug (get converter or secretary to help start your main combo)   3 cyberse gadget (I love this card for it’s ability to be 3 monsters in one, mainly to start combo)   3 widget kid (two for one to start combo)   3 backup secretary (powerful extender in this deck)   3 defcon bird (graveyard setup and monster on the field)   3 cyberse converter (quick body, extender or starter if necessary)   3 swap cleric (none of the link monsters in this deck need their attack points because you’re giving them to clock dragons so it’s just an easy draw)   1 stack reviver (extender, helped me out a lot)   1 dotscaper (easy to get out on the field, it’s also a two for one so use it)   1 latency (for the draw)   3 cynet fusion (key card in the deck)   3 cynet mining (search, sometimes clock wyvern, sometimes a way to get two monsters)   3 fusion conscription (quick access to clock wyvern)   2 cyberse clock dragon (win condition, one swing for the kill)   1 diplexer chimera (safey and latency)   1 code talker inverted (extender)   3 clock lizard (heart and soul of the deck, I couldn’t have made this combo work without it, also it’s banish effect is not a once per turn so you can stack multiple if you used extenders)   1 security dragon (if you used an extender then this can provide clearance)   1 secure gardna (fusion material, explained later)   1 clock spartoi (cynet fusion search)   1 link devotee (despicable-devotee)   1 link despicable (despicable-devotee)   1 linkguriboh (for the big dragon)   1 linkuribloh (for the big dragon)   The combo:    Materials: clock wyvern and a way to get two cyberses out (gadget also works in this spot), go second, it’s okay to have the clock wyvern in your hand because of fusion conscription.   Summon the two cyberses   Link cyberse one to make despicable   Link cyberse two to make devotee   Despicable eff tribute devotee to draw one and put one on the bottom   Devotee summons two tokens   Link one token for linkuriboh   Link likuriboh and despicable for clock spatoni   Spatoni searches cynet fusion (whatever you do do not use spatoni’s second effect)   Link other token for linguriboh   Link linguriboh to make secure guardna   Activate cynet fusion to fuse guardna with clock wyvern for a cyberse clock dragon   Link clock dragon with spatoni to make clock lizard   Lizard eff tribute self put clock dragon into extra deck then banish every link monster in your grave to make cyberse clock dragon again   Clock dragon then chain lizard   Lizard weakens all special summoned monsters your opponent owns by 400 points for every cyberse in the grave   Clock dragon mills cards on top of the deck to the grave for every link rating (link 2 = two cards for example) you used to summon it, if the combo was done normally then you’ll send 9 cards, for every card milled you gain 1000 attack points (if combo done normally then this totals up to 11500), attack a weakened monster and win game   Alt note, if you have two spare cyberses in your hand you can use cynet fusion to fuse them to summon your diplexer then have it tribute itself, lock the spells and traps out of the battle phase and recycle cynet fusion.   Alt note, use the extenders to help get more link monsters in the grave if possible to boost your clock dragon, clock lizard’s banished effect is not once per turn so you can use it multiple times in a turn allowing for you to stack a lot of debuffs and make it so that you to swing for game more easily.   I love the deck, the combo took some time to get used to but overall it’s really good and I find I'm able to end games very quickly and consistently using this combo.   (my record is 17500, if you use this deck then tell me yours!)

deck_excerpt: A decklist featuring the "Traptrix" archetype, an Insect- and Plant-type combination of monsters that make use of "Hole" Trap cards and spam the field
deck_description:
This is my take at building a "Traptrix" deck. The "Traptrix" archetype features a small arsenal of Level 4 monsters which not only interact with their own archetype but also search an play "Hole" Normal Trap cards quite extensively. Together with their Extra Deck monsters in form of two Link and two Xyz monsters, they stop the opposing monster summons to create an opening for attacks. But let us take a look at what cards I have thrown together for better understanding:

The Main Deck features of the following monster cards: Three copies of "Traptrix Myrmeleo" and three copies of "Traptrix Mantis" work as our Normal Summons, with "Traptrix Myrmeleo" searching the deck for a "Hole" Normal Trap card on Normal Summon, while "Traptrix Mantis" gives us access to a "Traptrix" monster from the deck when Normal Summoned. Both are also useful outside of being Normal Summoned with "Traptrix Myrmeleo" bringing an in-archetypal backrow removal effect while "Traptrix Mantis" can bounce the own backrow and set cards from the hand as a Quick Effect, which has some interaction with archetypes like "Artifacts" but mainly serves to dodge targeting effects like "Mystical Space Typhoon" or "Cosmic Cyclone" in this deck. One of the targets for the search effect of "Traptrix Mantis" is "Traptrix Ginalloa", the newest Main Deck monster and a solid member of the archetype overall. For the cost of sending one of your "Hole" Trap cards to the graveyard she can Special Summon herself from the hand, therefore giving you another body on the field if every works out without disruption while giving you another try at building a board if the Normal Summon was negated earlier that turn. She also can banish herself from the graveyard to recycle a Trap card from your graveyard which also help fighting the battle against the opposing summons. "Traptrix Ginalloa" also helps the deck by sending a Trap to the graveyard by giving a solid start to the last two "Traptrix" Main Deck monsters in this deck in form of two copies of "Traptrix Dionaea" and a single copy of "Traptrix Genlisea". "Traptrix Dionaea" is very useful since she offers more Trap recycling on Special Summon and can therefore bring the Trap back the "Traptrix Ginalloa" used while "Traptrix Dionaea" is also the "Traptrix" version of a "Monster Reborn" on legs when Normal Summoned. "Traptrix Genlisea" has only one effect, but she is no slouch either since she can tribute herself to fetch two Trap cards, one from the deck and one from the graveyard, to put onto your field. The rest of the Main Deck monsters is made up of three copies of "Parallel eXceed", which can Special Summon itself as a Level 4 monster when you summon your Link-1 monster in form of "Traptrix Sera" and then fetches another copy of itself from the deck which also enters the field as a Level 4 monster and therefore sets you up nicely to go into a Rank 4 Xyz summon. Lastly, I play three copies of "Ash Blossom & Joyous Spring" for the obvious use as a handtrap against deck searching effects the opponent might try to pull off.

The Spell card section, as you can see, is quite barren with only a single copy of "Double or Nothing!" which is used for the "Utopia Double" engine and basically allows you to produce a 10000 ATK beater as a Rank 4 Xyz monster. There are a few more Trap cards though: I run two copies of "Trap Trick" as a solid Trap card searching option, and its effect is also the reason why so many of the Trap cards are in the deck as a pair. "Time Space Trap Hole", "Bottomless Trap Hole", "Traptrix Trap Hole Nightmare", "Gravedigger's Trap Hole" and "Floodgate Trap Hole" all are in the deck at a copy count of two and all provide destruction, negation and/or control effects in various situations. The non-"Hole" Trap cards consist of three copies of "The Phantom Knights of Shade Brigandine" to gain additional bodies for Rank 4 Xyz summons and, more importantly, to trigger "Traptrix Sera" during your first turn without the delay you would normally have when playing Trap cards. An additional three copies of "Infinite Impermanence" keeps the opposing effect monsters at bay.

The Extra Deck looks as follows: Xyz-wise, there is one copy of "Traptrix Rafflesia" as field protection for your other "Traptrix" monsters and as a handy effect to fire off "Hole" Trap card directly from the deck, one copy of "Traptrix Allomerus" for various summoning schenanigans, the "Utopia Double" package featuring one copy of "Number 39: Utopia Double" and one copy of "Number 39: Utopia" to ram into your opponent for the aforementioned 10000 ATK, one copy of "Number 41: Bagooska the Terribly Tired Tapir" as a stall option,  one copy of "Tornado Dragon" as Quick Effect backrow removal, and one copy of "Abyss Dweller" to keep the opponent from using the graveyard. The Link monsters feature three copies of "Traptrix Sera", who is your main play-enabler which searches and summons/places monsters and Traps directly from the deck, one copy of "Traptrix Utricularia" as a fun little gimmick and solid option in grind games, one copy each of "Knightmare Phoenix", "Knightmare Cerberus", and "Knightmare Unicorn" to destroy backrow/frontrow respectively while having the big boy to send things back into the deck, and one copy of "Borrelsword Dragon" for the usual beatdown/game-ending Link-4 play.

While certainly not my favorite deck playstyle-wise, I do have to admit that these carnivorous girls can put quite a nasty board together, and the newest support cards helps them both in making the deck more viable while also providing the creative players with more tools and gimmicks to make use of. The times when "Traptrix" only really worked as an engine together with some other archetype are definitely over, they form a solid deck that rightly deserve the amount of fans it gathered over the years. If you want to know some more about the "Traptrix" archetype, feel free to visit my archetype analysis about them by clicking the link here: https://cubiccreativity.wordpress.com/2019/12/07/archetype-analysis-traptrix/

deck_excerpt: It's a deck based on sheep... I don't know what you want out of me.
deck_description: So this was a deck I made that I don't exactly remember the why as to it's creation. It's a deck that is built on the very simple gimmick of sheep-based monsters, and what they can do. It's by no means a "great" deck, (honestly, I don't think really any of the decks I build are "great", but that's neither here nor there.)  The main strategy of the deck I find to be the most useful is utilizing the tokens of Scapeghost and Sheep Cloud to either go into link plays leading into "Unchained Abomination", a fusion summon of "Dragonecro Nethersoul Dragon", or a synchro summon of "Armades, Keeper of Boundaries". But the funny enjoyment of beating your opponent with "Token Stampede" seemed to have been what the original build was created on before I attempted to make it... somewhat work consistently.  Overall though, it's a slow deck that isn't by any means "competitive" or "good", but it's still a weird gimmick that I wanted to show off as I try to backup the decks I've built on EDOPro.

deck_excerpt: This is an early built "Abhyss" deck that tries to bully your opponent using the boss monster of the deck. Not a great build, but an idea.
deck_description: Abhyss seemed like an interesting deck to me, a deck that effectively tribute summons from the graveyard was something I felt like could be a fun concept to build around. So I gave it a shot and, while the build definitely has potential to be something decent, the amount of dead draws that I found the deck gives me is a little more than it's worth.  This build focuses probably more than it should on using "Ogdoabyss, Deity of the Abhyss"s destruction effect,  and after blowing up the field, beating your opponent with a 3100 ATK point monster, and, if that doesn't work, just using "Evil Dragon Ananta" late game to finish the job.
Dragonmaid Sheou is your best winning condition.

Continuing to just... deck unload here, we have one of my favorite archetypes on design alone, Vehicroids, a deck that I wish was better but Konami refuses to give proper support for. This build definitely had "Barbaroid, the Ultimate Battle Machine" in mind, but summoning it has been the least consistent thing about it, so now I just kinda play it to attack into things with a beefed up "Truckroid" and kinda hope for the best. I think if I am to rebuild this deck ever, I'd probably have a different focus in mind when building so as not to have the main strategy be probably the worst one to go into.

Union Hangar is a 1 card ABC Dragon Buster, which means you can just run loads of hand traps. Using ZW - Pegasus Twin Saber in combination with Union Carrier provides the deck with an on field negate which it usually lacks unless summoning Cyber Dragon Infinity. Dweller provides protection on both players turns and ABC Dragon Buster ability to flee allows you to make powerful Link Monsters on your turn like Apollusa and Borrelsword. Want to see the deck in action!?!

So I play tested with the last list and found that 4 normal summons is a little too much. I have cut the 2 copies of Kuribandit, as well as the Eldlich stuff and I wanted to with more of a pure Draco Route. I do play some Monarch cards and a spellbook engine. Domain got cut to 1 copy as I found it clashes with Diagram, which is the more important field spell. This build could benefit from a Set Rotation, but I decided not to include it because the space is tight. I wanted to go with a 40 card build and Upstart would be the 41st card kekw. Also, the inclusion of Metaltron because this deck needs a decent boss monster. I found that sometimes the deck has trouble getting that big push for game and Dinomight, Ignis and Maiden sometimes (and regularly) isn't enough to push for game. Metaltron helps out with the potential to be immune to everything but also being pretty big, and with Diagram/Dreith on the field it might take a turn or two before your opponent can out him. Overall I am much happier with this build overall, and in my testing has been a little more powerful as well with the help of Metaltron and some of the newer additions. Hope you like the update.

deck_name: Photon Control - The Other Side of a Galaxy
deck_excerpt: Galaxy / Photon is a deck that normally sits on OTKing and hitting hard, but when you look at the other side of the cards a slower version might be mo
deck_description: Galaxy or Photon is an Xyz archetype that can make a powerful OTK, the truth is that the deck has interesting things like access to Cyber Dragon Infinity or the fact of having 4 archetypes working in one, but that's all. That was until I saw a Photon Change card, a trap with good effect that will almost always increase your resources and there I thought if I did a more Control version of the Deck and so we got to this beautiful deck, the truth is quite fun and I think it is very customizable that's why I brought it here.Monsters. Monsters Galaxy-Eyes Photon Dragon: Heart of the Deck at all, most of the cards synergize with him or his family, all 3 copies are necessary. Galaxy Knight: At first I thought it was a bad card, but the ability to not use the normal summon from the Deck makes this card a great play. Galaxy Soldier: Deck searcher which can summon Cyber Dragon Infinity. Photon Trasher: Good monster to summon. Photon Vanisher: Of the best cards on the deck, it is summoned almost always in addition to add a Galaxy-Eyes. Photon Advancer: Reverse Trasher. Orbital Photon: The true searcher of the archetype. Photon Lizard: A copy is fine to add combo pieces, unfortunately it takes away the possibility of summon Knight. Photon Sanctuary: Very good card, you can use it to summon Galaxy-Eyes, use Photon Change effect and the most useful, summon the Link. Galaxy Expedition: Very good card to win a high monster. Photon Stream of Destruction: A galaxy-eyes is easy to summon so it will almost always be usable, the gain of being used on the enemy turn gives a great bonus to this versión of the deck. Photon Change: The card that started it all, is a trap yes but it is quite good it can take advantage of monsters that your opponent is going to destroy and gain more resources such as a Galaxy-Eyes that you need, and if you use the Galaxy-Eyes this card will give you double power, well in case you need it, the only bad thing is that it self-destructs for no reason. Tachyon Transmigration: Negation of the archetype is like a Stream of Destruction but it negates, and with the plus of negating more than one effect, returning the cards to the Deck and being able to be used from the hand. Extra Deck Full Armor Photon Dragon: Switch to a Galaxy Xyz, for destruction and 4000 ATK is pretty good. Prime Photon Dragon: OTK Moment. Galaxy-Eyes Cipher Dragon: It can help ... I swear. Hope Harbinger: Very good negation for the Deck in first turn. Galaxy-Eyes Tachyon Dragon: It can help with some cheese games, I still take it for the tramp. Galaxy-Eyes Photon Lord: Second option to negation on first turn. Cyber ​​Dragon's: Infinity is great and being able to summon it so easily with Soldier makes it mandatory for the Deck. Starliege Lord Galaxion: Take advantage of Level 4 to summon Galaxy-Eyes from the Deck if it is not in hand. Starliege Paladynamo: OTK Moment. Starliege Photon Blast Dragon: Level 4 will almost always summon this to put the Galaxy-Eyes on the field, protect it and summon it again. Galaxy-Eyes Solflare Dragon: The link is easy to invoke with Sanctuary so it is always good to carry copies of it, it recovers resources and it can also destroy cards. Union Carrier: Another good Link, can put Orbital. Other Things Impermanence and Warning Point: A few good traps help the deck, in my case Impermanence is possibly the best current trap and Warning Point is quite good, to negate effect, summon of various monsters.Other Options Other Options: Galaxy Monstes: Afterglow Dragon is easy to summon and gain recurse, sometimes brick, also is more  OTK that a control, Wizard is good, he changes levels and searches but he is like Lizard and almost always worse, Cloudragon is a good card that can revive Galaxy-Eyes and he is also a "Galaxy-Eyes" that can be Normal Summon, Neo Galaxy-Eyes can make “things”, Galaxy Satellite Dragon another link although it is not so good. Galaxy Spell/Traps: Photon Hand is an interesting card it can steal Monsters although it blocks you if you do not have the Galaxy-Eyes so that's why they are not used, Galaxy Trance is a bit instaXYZ, Galaxy Zero is the reborn of the archetype. Number 97: Draglubion is one of that cards that can do some interesting things with, Numeron Dragon and C107 but it’s not that good in this version, also with have Barian Force if you just want the C107. Generics: Guardian of Order is sometimes good to have but not that good a 3, Not just Cosmic Cyclone you can use Twin Twisters, Space Typhoon or Galaxy Cyclone this are for destroy Backrow Because the deck is not that good in that, Zeuz is just to good.   Thing you should Know As I said before you can put the traps you want I put those because they are the ones I like the most but if you want you can put yours. Learn how to use Photon Change, seriusly. You should also know that Xyz to use at all times, using the right one can help a lot. As I said before, the deck is highly customizable, there are several Galaxy, Photon, Cipher, Galaxy Eyes cards and these can give different touches to the deck. Upcoming decks? S-Force: The newest thing in the trunk of ideas, it is not very special but currently I am really enjoying playing with this deck. Abhyss: Well F, I had ideas but they did not work so well and I would not want to do something of the lot so I’m keep thinking. True Draco Crystal: As I said before, practically ready, I will only think about uploading it this month or the next if I do not have ideas. Remake of the Best Fusion Deck: A little bit the same, it is ready although I think it is more likely that this will upload it this month. Also first day of March. If you would like to see one of this deck, dont forget to comment.

deck_excerpt: Attempting to abuse field spells, one card at a time. Proof of Concept, definitely needs tweaking.
deck_description: Actually! While I'm "deck dumping", I would like to share this... monstrosity of a deck concept, because, I feel, in theory, it could work, I just don't have it quite down yet. The idea is that there are field spells that can help by special summoning from your deck, or adding a card to your hand, then using those cards to go into other plays. Alternatively, we can use certain field spells to slow down or stop some of your opponent's plays. This is definitely not the theoretical "best" build, moreso a proof of concept, and to a degree it works, but I feel like it can definitely be better with a bit of tweaking.

deck_excerpt: A deck of warriors that focuses on powering up weaker monsters
deck_description: I first made this deck back in 2014 when I cam back to the game after a lengthy hiatus back when I played through duel network and I wanted to make a deck that used one of my favourite cards, Command Knight, so I searched through the data base for cards that would work well with it hitting upon a strategy that involved using Marauding Captain to form a lock stopping my weaker monsters from being destroyed in battle while powering them up through the effects of The A. Forces and Command Knight. Fast forward two (or maybe three? I'm getting forgetful in my old age) and pendulum summoning is just being released and my little lizard brain goes "no likey" so I decide to take another hiatus from the game (until either the Valkyries or Backup Gardna are released) up until the Steam winter sale at the end of last year where Yu-Gi-Oh Legacy of the Duelist: Link Evolution was on sale so I decided to pick it up and give it a play rediscovering my love for the game (still hate pendulum summoning though) and with that we arrive to the current incarnation of what is now a seven year old deck.           The core tactic hasn't changed, you power up your weaker (and stronger) monsters through card effects while protecting them from battle with Marauding Captain. The original deck had Absolute Crusader, Sword Master and Dark Blade the Captain of the Evil World who have since been replaced (partly because I now have better options and partly because I actually forgot the actual contents of the deck) and obviously no link monsters, speaking of whichFerocious Flame Swordsmanis a big boon to the deck as it also powers up the warriors but can also resurrect fallen warriors if it's not in your extra monster zone while Black Luster Soldier - Soldier of Chaosacts as yet another boss monster but for the most part you'll be relying on your level 3 and 4 monsters to do most of the heavy lifting.     The Attribute Knights are just there to make Black Luster Soldier - Envoy of the Beginning easier to access although there is a nice combo with an empty hand, Armageddon Knight, Swift Gaia the Fierce Knight and The Warrior Returning Alive where you summon Armageddon Knight, send Gaia then using The Warrior Returning Alive to then summon Gaia from your empty hand, not reliable by any means but a fun combo nonetheless. I will admit that I've not managed to test Dawn Knight in the deck yet but it shouldn't be too different to its dark counterpart.

The Aromage archetype has always been my favorite. I picked up Yu Gi Oh via Duel Links after a 10 year hiatus and so much has changed. Well, this deck was the only free to play one I actually enjoyed on the app. I was excited to learn that it has even more support outside of the limited format. I decided to give this archetype a competitive try and it fairs somewhat well.  This deck recycles very well (if you manage to keep all spell/traps on the field, hence running Ibicella for targeting) Maintaining high LP is key in order to ensure success. for monster that you find difficult to destroy via effect/battle Teardrop can tribute them for an attack boost and help clear the field.     Edit: Well, looked up other Aroma decks and everything I've listed has been done before and there are similar decks... Apologies  With Aromaseraphy's Majoram, Rosemary, and Jasmine, Ibicella, and Teardrop on the field you have full control. Blessed Winds recycles all of your plant cards and A. Jasmine grants you the ability to re-add  a shuffled monster to the hand (works best for Angelica/Majoram)  This deck isn't full proof by any means, but it is definitely fun to use. It also requires a bit of patience as there are a lot of moving pieces however, with practice, it becomes easier to navigate. I'm not well versed enough to go into more detail about how to use the deck, but as I learn more of the meta I will be updating my decklist summaries. Thanks!

deck_excerpt: A BLS deck that is as competitive as I could make it. Very fun to play and impcantations make it more consistent. Non-meta.
deck_description: Read the ''Important'' part Black Luster Soldier is my favourite archetype so I have been trying to make a powerful BLS deck and here it is! Please tell me your suggestions so I can make this deck as good as it can be. This deck uses no banned cards. If you can't get Twilight BLS replace it with sacred BLS and then add another card to the side deck. IMPORTANT: I was having problems putting cards in the side deck, after super soldier reborn is the side deck. This means that the monster to spells/traps ratio will be incorrect. Link Black Luster Soldier is purely optional; (If you own it though use it) because its very exspensive and you could accidentally banish by pot of extra's effect. Impcantations:  I used them to increase consistency in the deck. There is no pencilplume, for syntheisis can special summon from the grave. 1x bookstone so you can add syntheisis from your graveyard to your hand. Rest of the Main deck  x2 Super Soldier Reborn: Once you side in Sacred BLS you can use envoy as the target and sacred as the special summon, therefore triggering Sacred's effect. 1x Envoy of chaos: This card will probably only be used as link and ritual material but if your opponent is using monsters with 3100+ atk you can always add it to your hand with reinforcement of the army. 1x Foolish Burial: If you don't get Super BLS in your hand you can use it to send super to the grave and bring it back with synthesis. Also it can help you summon twilight and envoy BLS.  1x Impcantation Inception: if the only ritual materials available are impcantations add it to your hand with candoll. Side Deck [15 cards] The side deck is basically an arsenal of handtraps, 3x of the card you want to summon with Reborn (Sacred BLS), and Arisen gaia which is a target for Super BLS. Extra deck [15 cards] Mainly just so you can use pot of extra but Dark Rebellion and link BLS are summonable and powerful.

deck_excerpt: Going second deck that went 5-3 at the FEB EXTRVA
deck_description: THIS IS A GOING SECOND BUILD!!!     This deck is all about breaking your opponents board and even OTKing them on the crackback or setting up a barrier lock with some interaction on their next turn. I used this deck this past weekend (2/28/21) and finished 54th with an 8-3 record. Lu Feng makes this deck much better then before BLOV. Drawing any ancient warrior along with Lu Feng auto puts him on the field. Not only that but having a tri-brigade monster create double dragon lords also opens it up to summon easy plus with a 500 attk boost. You can also switch from a going second to a going first strat pretty easy with this deck. Just sub out the three Loyal Guan Yuns, alpha, and the lightning storms for the books, crackdowns, and either the barrier/ dark simorgh or one of the other plus another card. Going first you do have to worry about nib! If you can go full combo you should able to end on Simorgh + Barrier + Double dragon lord (bounce to hand) + Lu Feng (destroy quick eff during main 1). Also this absolutely punished any other tri-brigade builds I played. The fact that most of the ancient warriors are wind is just icing on the cake. Finally, a very under rated card that has a lot of synergy with tri-brigade is Sun Mou. His eff to send a card from hand or field to grave to add an ancient warrior monster opens the door to send kit or nervall thus openning up tri-brigade while you set up your ancient warrior plays as well. Overall very happy with how this deck performed!
