deck_excerpt: It's a deck full of my dreams... Quite easy
deck_description:
The deck idea is nearly entirely from YT. The ideal hand is Torn Scale and Stygian Street Patrol and other 3 spells/traps, which you first have to set them all on the field.
  1. The deck starts off with Torn Scales using its effect to discard Stygian (Or put it in the graveyard anyhow) and dump Ancient Cloak (From deck) and search Silent Boots using Ancient Cloak's effect.
  2. Special summon Silent Boots using its own effects and link summon them into Cherubini.
  3. Activate Cherubini's effect to dump Fiendish Rhino Warrior, which then its effects activate to dump Archfiend Heiress, which allows you to add the Infernity Archfiend to your hand.
  4. Activate Silent Boot's effect in the graveyard to banish itself and add the trap, Shade Brigandine, and chain with that to activate Torn Scales effect and special summon it from the graveyard.
  5. Activate Shade Brigandine (Since you have no traps in your graveyard, you can activate it the turn you set the card) and summon itself as a level 4, dark monster.
  6. Activate the effect of Stygian Street Patrol to banish itself and special summon a fiend monster in your hand, which would be Infernity Archfiend.
  7. Activate Infernity Archfiend to search for Infernity Necromancer.
  8. Link summon Proxy F Magician using any of those Cherubini and one other effect monster on your field. (Your field should have Cherubini, Archfiend, Torn Scale, and Shade Brigandine. In the hand, there should be Infernity Necromancer)
  9. Activate the effect of Proxy F Magician to fusion summon Starving Venom Fusion Dragon using rest of the monsters on your field, to a zone which Proxy F Magician points to.
  10. Activate the second effect of Proxy F Magician (Special summon a monster with less than 1000 ATK from your hand when a fusion monster was special summoned to a zone this card points to) to special summon Infernity Necromancer from hand.
  11. Activate Infernity Necromancer's effect to special summon Infernity Archfiend from graveyard, and activate its effect to add Infernity Patriarch to hand.
  12. Link summon Cross-Sheep using Infernity Necromancer and Proxy F Magician and special summon Infernity Patriarch to a zone Cross-Sheep points to, using its own effect. (Cross-Sheep should be pointing at Starving Venom and Infernity Patriarch)
  13. Then, use Cross-Sheep's effect to special summon Necromancer back from the graveyard.
  14. Overlay Patriarch and Archfiend into Dugares, and use its effect to special summon its own material, Archfiend.
  15. Use Archfiend's effect to add Infernity Launcher to hand, and just put it on field.
  16. Link summon Saryuja using all monsters on your field, except the Necromancer. (Still hasn't used the effects yet)
  17. If you want to take the chance and try using the 3rd effect of Saryuja, (Draw 4, put back 3) you can try, but I am not going over that since that is based on luck.
  18. Activate Necromancer's effect to special summon Archfiend, then its effect to add Infernity Mirage to hand.
  19. Activate second effect of Saryuja (Special summon from hand) and summon Mirage to the field.
  20. Link summon Apollousa using Saryuja, Archfiend, and Necromancer. (To empty the field a little and send archfiend and necromancer to the graveyard)
  21. Use Mirage's effect of special summon Archfiend and Necromancer from the graveyard.
  22. Use Archfiend's effect to add Infernity Avenger to hand, and discard it using Infernity Launcher's first effect.
  23. Activate Necromancer's effect to special summon launcher.
  24. Link summon Halqifibrax using Avenger and Archfiend, and activate its effect to summon Infernity Wildcat from the deck.
  25. Overlay Necromancer and Wildcat into Rebarian Shark. (Material of Z-ARC)
  26. Link summon Verte Anaconda using Halqifibrax and Rebarian Shark.
  27. Activate Launcher's effect to special summon Necromancer and Avenger.
  28. Special summon Archfiend from the graveyard using Necromancer's effect, and search Infernity Paranoia.
  29. Activate Paranoia on Necromancer to summon Infernity Conjurer from the deck.
  30. Synchro summon Hundred Eyes Dragon using Archfiend, Conjurer, and Avenger and activate its effect to banish Mirage from the graveyard and gain its effect.
  31. Use Hundred Eyes Dragon's effect (Infernity Mirage's effect) to tribute itself and special summon Necromancer and Avenger.
  32. Special summon Archfiend using Necromancer's effect and use its effect to search Infernity Barrier or Suppression.
  33. Use Conjurer's own effect to special summon itself from the graveyard.
  34. Synchro summon Shooting Riser Dragon using Avenger, Conjurer, and Necromancer.
  35. Activate Riser's effect upon summon to send Supreme King Dragon Darkwurm to the graveyard, and Riser becomes level 3. (Which doesn't matter if you're not planning a Calamity)
  36. Activate Verte Anaconda's second effect to pay 2000 LP and send Miracle Synchro Fusion to the graveyard, and banish Number 71: Rebarian Shark (XYZ Dragon monster), Hundred Eyes Dragon (Synchro Dragon Monster), Starving Venom Fusion Dragon (Fusion Dragon Monster), and Supreme King Dragon Darkwurm (Pendulum Dragon Monster) to the graveyard to summon Supreme King Z-ARC from your extra deck, obliterating your opponent's field while getting at least 4 negates. (Infernity Barrier and 2400 ATK Apollousa)

deck_excerpt: Experimenting to increase consistency here--might have made some questionable decisions,,, let me know what you guys think
deck_description: Update: I added back in 2 Citadels and 1 Institution as well as 1 Terraforming for searching, while also moving Archfiend Eccentrick and Left Hand to the side deck (see the changes below). Had a hard time letting go of Archfiend Eccentrick from the main deck as it was in the first pendulum deck I used after watching one of Trif's videos, but having it in your starting hand is Death. I also underestimated the field spell's ability as a combo extender if I draw into since it just collects counters and has a built in protection effect. It makes recovery possible if the rest of my board gets cleared while my hand is empty. I explain my logic behind all of the cards below, but here's a description of the combos before getting into all of that if you aren't familiar: Most of the combos revolve around using Servant of Endymion, Reflection of Endymion, and Chronograph Sorcerer to special summon monsters from the scales while saving your pendulum summon for the end, along with Magicians' Souls/Jester Confit as special summons, so that you can link into Crowley for the Spellbook engine **if you still have targets**.  Usually you will use Servant to special summon Jackal King so you can start build Spell Counters, and also to protect yourself against a potential Nibiru/Gamma, but there might be instances where you can think of a better monster to summon, like, for example, Magical Abductor to search for Magicians' Souls for your Restage engine. Remember that there are only 5 spellbook cards in the deck, as well as 4 potential targets for Crowley. If you used Pot of Desires, check the banished stack to make sure that there are not 2 or more targets in there or else Crowley will be useless. If you don't go into Crowley, then try to go into Selene if you have the desired monster in your graveyard, or Saryuja if you have 4 disposable monsters on the field (generally don't use Jackal King/Mighty Master to go into Saryuja unless you can still use your pendulum summon to bring them back out, but do that ASAP). Use One for One and Magicians' Souls with Selene in mind. If you don't have the desired negates in your hand, or, for One for One, if you have to choose between a negate boss monster and a scale that plusses, send that negate to the GY, because you can use Selene to bring them back. Also remember that if you send Reflection to the GY, you can summon her on the opponents turn to bounce back one of their cards. Try to avoid normal summoning unless its Spellbook Magician of Prophecy (Blue Boy), because that allows you to choose him as a viable/non-dead target for Crowley, because you thin 3 cards from your deck and get a guaranteed Draw 2 if Crowley resolves. If you have to, normal summon Magical Abductor to build counters to search for Souls. This way you can pitch a negate to the GY, but then if/when you summon Crowley: don't use Blue Boy as a target. Use Spellbook of Secrets, Knowledge, and Power. Worst case scenario: you can still get another spell counter and 1000 attack on a monster (this is explained below). I say "ash bait" a lot, but remember that, since you have a few avenues to try and get to your end board, the role of ash bait tends to shift around depending on which engine is the most easily accessible with your starting hand Main Deck: The core monsters for all of the Endymion decks I've posted on here have mostly been the same, although I reduced Cerberus to 1 again since I only mostly use it to bait ash, and if I don't start with it, I usually draw into Jackal King easily enough anyways, in which case I sometimes use it to search Garuda. Another questionable choice I might have made was Magister, which I'm running at 1, because even though its not high priority I use it for recovery if I get board-wiped with Zeus and all my pendulum monsters are in the extra deck, its also nice to summon reflection on the opponents turn to bounce back their summons if I'm unable to draw into my negate-heavy monsters. Restage Engine: Pretty self-explanatory stuff here. I'm running 3 Restage and 1 Right Hand in the main deck. I'm keeping Left Hand in the side deck against trap-heavy opponents. With the Restage engine, I'm actually running 2 souls and 1 confit instead of 3 of either. Obviously I feel like Souls should be mandatory for the Restage engine, but I'm giving priority normal summon to Magical Abductor to build counters to search for Souls, and I'm also running One for One to summon Souls and potentially set a target for Selene in the GY from my hand. One for One is also just another spell to build counters that's rarely ever dead and adds to my field while also giving me counters, which I really like. The single Jester confit is there instead of a third Souls as a free special summon if I ever start with souls in hand, or if I'm deliberately avoiding a normal summon so that I can use Blue Boy as one of my targets for Crowley. This is one of the reasons I'm running the Chronograph engine (free spell counter, free special summon, and if I have a second Chronograph in hand, then its *another* free special summon if not just a free target for One for One). **edit: I actually reduced the Chronograph engine from 3 to 2 to add in Reasoning, with the reasoning (lol) that its still usually special summon for the most part as well as a spell counter either way, therefore still usually accomplish the purpose of Chronograph Sorcerer for me, but also because, if I draw into Reasoning, vs the 3rd copy of Chronograph, and I had already used Chronograph's effect, or banished Timegazer with Desires, then Reasoning is still live in my hand (I'm really trying to eliminate dead cards as much as I can without affecting the versatility of my monsters)** Spellbook Engine: My spellbook engine used to be 2 Blue Boy, 2 Secrets, 1 Knowledge, but *because* I'm giving priority normal summon to Abductor, I wanted to reduce Blue Boy. I didn't want to eliminate him entirely, because he's nice ash bait, but also is one of the preferred targets for Crowley alongside Secrets and Knowledge. Secrets is still at 2 because with 3 targets in the deck its rarely dead, but at 3 I feel like it wouldn't help that much. Spellbook of *Power* may seem like an odd inclusion in the deck (and honestly it might be, if you guys know a better Spellbook spell that has a better chance of being live in my hand lmk), however, my reasoning for this is that, if Blue Boy gets ash'd, I want to give myself the option to still go into Crowley, without drawing chance giving me a dead card (another blue boy would run the risk of me grabbing a dead blue boy in my hand with Crowley's effect if I already normal summoned blue boy), and most of the other Spellbook cards seem to be pretty reliant on having Spellbook spell cards already in my hand. With Power, however, if I can still search for a Spellbook spell if I just destroy another monster in battle, and it will also still give me counters (it's pretty low priority though with respect to Crowley's effect and in this would be a worst-case scenario for me). Of course there's Upstart, Instant Fusion for spell counters and also handtrap protection with Millennium Eyes and 2 Pot of Desires instead of 3, because I'm normally getting enough draws and thinning out my deck with both the Restage and Spellbook Engines, and I can even go into Saryuja with little difficulty without pendulum summoning. Extra Deck: In terms of the Extra Deck, its usually the same every time I post it, but I made a few changes and I'll just explain all my decisions here: there's Underworld Goddess for that "extra deck kaiju" business, which I can summon on the opponents turn using their monster if I have Masquerena on field (kinda like unchained except it doesn't target which is really nice and probably my favorite play with Masquerena). It also has a nice protection effect and can negate a summon from the GY. I have Accesscode for the OTK and high ATK. Selene to climb into Accesscode but also for counters to extend my plays-- its also nice to summon Reflection from the GY to bounce and opponents monster (really any card but usually monster), and its also a really nice stall card if nothing else, especially if I summon it with Masquerena. I only really use Apollousa if my hand is just really shit, I've used the spellbook engine and I don't have enough material to draw 4 off of Saryuja, and then I also have Knightmare unicorn for non-destruction removal on the opponents turn. Knightmare Phoenix if the opponent does something like Anti-Spell/Imperial Order/TCBOO etc., the Odd-Eyes package, Cross-Sheep with the Odd-Eyes Package so I can climb into Selene, Artemis if I start with a normal summonable pendulum monster and Knowledge and so I can still draw 2 if I don't start with souls/blue boy/confit as well. There's also a nice combo with Artemis and restage, where I can special summon either souls or confit, link into Artemis, re-summon souls/confit with restage and link into Crowley to still have all my preferred Spellbook targets usable. Side Deck: For the side deck, theres Pankratops, which is another one of my answers to Anti-Spell/Imperial Order, and of course red reboot. My blind second card that I usually side in is Evenly Matched, and I'll normally side out Cerberus, Spellbook of Power and either Right Hand or Left Hand depending on the match up. **Didn't think I'd have to do this but: The reason I'm running Evenly vs Lightning Storm or Harpie's or Raigeki/Dark Hole is because: It doesn't target, it doesn't destroy, and it isn't once per turn. So if it resolves, worst case scenario you have to play through 2 disruptions (one on field and one in hand), best case scenario you can basically OTK. If it doesn't resolve, its because the opponent negated it, which means they would have negated any of the other above mentioned spells, which means: best case scenario they used their one spell/trap negate and you can still do full combo with Mighty Master to blow up their board, or worst case scenario they still had 50 billion spell/trap negates and you couldn't do jack anyways** **Edit: I used to have 3 Nibiru because of Dragon Link, and that ridiculous Deskbot/Halq/Auroradon combo, but I realized that, not only can nibiru be negated, but that if I don't start with Nibiru in hand, its better to draw into Sphere Mode to break the opponents board rather than Nibiru** Against monster heavy decks, I'm using Dark Ruler No More instead of Droplet, because I don't want to reduce my hand at all for follow up plays. The 2 Cosmic Cyclones are for match-ups against Eldlich.

Tired of the same zoo Eldlich combo or decklist? Are you tired to see your opponents plays the game? Your prayers were heard!!  Today I come with one of the most disgusting  list: Zoodiac Kaiju, The infamous  KAZOO!! This is a totally control build that prevents you opponent to build his own board.  Zoodiac is a formidable engine because it is  a lair of one card combos, vary recursive and a small (but strong) engine. Zoodiac  Trident can pop up any card on the field, also becoming a good card to going first (disrupt any plays in the opponents turn), or a going second card  to get in the Vespenato. This engine is so amazing that if you want to go in more agressive way, you can also use Megaclops to deal a massive damage.  Kaiju are notorius to disrupted big boards ( Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess, Red-Eyes Dark Dragoon and similars) and with a help of  Interrupted Kaiju Slumber , our job  become incredibly easy.  Ah... and here we have a lot , A LOT  of hand traps  to deals with draws ( Droll & Lock Bird), effect of the field (Ghost Ogre & Snow Rabbit), or GY in general ( Ghost Belle & Haunted Mansion and Skull Meister). The main engine is effective and small , so handtraps can fit perfectely in this control build.     For the final words, I know that Divine Arsenal AA-ZEUS - Sky Thunder will be perfect and logical to add in this deck  but... I don't have it =/ however , if you have, feel free to use it and be happy with it. I hope you like it my crazy idea.

Disclaimer:I'm not a pro nor a competitive player of any forms so my deck could not be perfect,do all the changes you like  The strategy for this deck is as basic as it gets: special summon E-Hero Sunrise as fast as you can.  Sunrise can fetch a Miracle Fusion from your deck to your hand,gives all your monster 200 Atk for each attribute you control and, once per turn, you can destroy a card on the field when another Hero monster you control declare an attack. From Sunrise you can then fuse the Omni Hero you need in that situation.  Blazeman can get you a Poli when summoned,Dark Mist a Mask Change (only when special summoned), Solid Soldier can special summon another hero when it's normal summoned (and special summons a Hero from the graveyard when sent there from the field by a spell card) and Liquid can let you draw 2 cards then discard 1 when used for a fusion (also special summons a Hero from the grave when norma summoned).  The Hand Trapa can be varied.  concerning the Extra Deck:  -I recommend at least 1 copy of each Omni Hero so that you can use Super Poli on whatever your opponent may summon  -Dark Law can be a pain in the ass by distrupting grave setup and destroyng a card in the hand when the opponent add a card from the deck and Acid destroys the backrow when brought out (so I like to use it with Zero since he destroys all opponents monster when sent from the field to the grave)  -Predaplant Anaconda is there for when you don't draw any fusion card.  Well,I think that's all; remember it's a deck I made for fun because it's my favourite archetype but if you have suggestions on how to make it competitive please let me know. Have Fun!

It's been a while since I've updated my Pr-K deck so why not do it right now A few new additions
  • Speedriod Taketomburg: I needed a new extender to help turbo out verte without breaking my board
  • Droll and Lock Bird: This deck is arguably a control deck so to help stop your opponents from making a strong board this card definitely helps
  • Ancient Leaf: Basically a Pot of Greed if you resolve Dropsies
  • Fusion Sage/Polymerization: Crucial for making combos or rebuilding your board
  • Triple Tactics Talent: Your Response to Handtraps on Prank-Kids
Now a few things before I dive into the combos, the first is it is now possible to rebuild your board with the help of Poly. You see you can either skip your normal summon by fusion summoning or wait till your board breaks and then fusion summon. Also if you summon doodle you almost always want to search place unless you activated place before. Finally, be patient with exceed this deck takes a different turn if your opponent has hand traps or not.

  • Plague Spreader
  • Fusion Sage if you have Poly

deck_excerpt: A cool toolboxy deck that has some neat plays
deck_description: This deck has some really cool synergy, nephthys provide a powerful resource loop of summoning conductor to summon devotee from deck to then summon disciple from deck to search a card, which can be a conductor to do the same thing the following turn to make armored kappa for an easy zeus. Fire kings work very well with this because both are decks centered around destroying cards, and Tri-brigade is useful for making big link pushes and also getting out the simorgh link to get stormwinds during the end phase. Impcantations help with searching for the parts of the nephthys engine and then can be tributed as to get around their extra deck lock. I chose ghost ogre as a good handtrap because not only can you trigger some fire king effects off of it, but you can also use e-tele to get more link material on board, and gamma is an all around good handtrap. Wicked eraser is in the side deck because it could be cool, but I couldn't make the space for it.  Hope you all enjoy, and feedback is welcome as always.

Drytron took a massive hit losing two essential combo pieces. Union Carrier was banned which was a search for the whole deck and Cyber Angel Benten was limited which gave the deck endless resources. Now that those cards are out of the picture Drytron are mid-tier but still very playable and still competitive. 

 

     Drytron can still break dragon link and virtual world boards and can keep up with the meta. Now that Cyber Angel Benten and Union Carrier are either banned or limited there are now new combos. With these combos you get to utilize cards like Beatrice, Lady of the Eternal, Cyber Angel Idaten, the Megalith engine, and with Drytron Mu-Beta Fafnir around the corner Drytron is still a very playable strategy.  

    Now with all that in mind let's get into combo Number one.  Combo Number One  

   For this combo need access to Cyber Angel Benten + Drytron Zeta Aldhibah  

 but this can change depending on your hand.  

     Use Drytron Zeta Aldhibah effect in the hand to discard Cyber Angel Benten 

 then add Meteonis Drytron and Manju of the Ten Thousand Hands with the effect of Cyber Angel Benten and Drytron Zeta Aldhibah. Normal summon Manju of the Ten Thousand Hands adding Megalith Phul to hand. Using Meteonis Drytron summon Megalith Phul (tribute Zeta) triggering the effect to add back Cyber Angel Benten.  

(Now Megalith Phul will become level 6 because of its effect). Activate Megalith Phul’s effect discard Cyber Angel Benten to summon Megalith Ophiel from deck triggering its effect to add another Megalith Phul to hand also Cyber Angel Benten effect to add Cyber Angel Idaten to hand. Use Megalith Ophiel effect to summon Cyber Angel Idaten from hand using itself and Manju of the Ten Thousand Hands. 

The summon of Idaten will trigger its effect adding back to hand Meteonis Drytron. 

Overlay Megalith Phul and Cyber Angel Idaten for Beatrice, Lady of the Eternal. 

 Activate Beatrice, Lady of the Eternal effect detaching Cyber Angel Idaten then sending one monster to GY. I’ll choose Drytron Alpha Thuban (because I have no Herald of Perfection in hand or GY, but the card can change depending on your hand) when Drytron Alpha Thuban is sent to GY activate its effect discard the Megalith Phul in hand to summon the Drytron Alpha Thuban back which will trigger its effect to search Herald of Perfection adding it to hand. Use the Meteonis Drytron to summon Cyber Angel Idaten back from GY triggering her effect to search Dawn of the Herald. Then use Dawn of the Herald tributing off Cyber Angel Idate to summon the Herald of Perfection. When Dawn of the Herald and Cyber Angel Idate are sent to GY it triggers their effects. Chain link one Cyber Angel Idate, chain link two Dawn of the Herrald. Cyber Angel Idate will increase the stats of all ritual monster you control, and Dawn will add Idaten back to the hand for another negate. Now during your opponent's turn when you use your Idate negate (or Herald sending it to GY to negate) Quick effect Beatrice detaches one material to send Eva to GY triggering its effect to banish up to 2 other LIGHT Fairy monsters from your field and/or GY; add the same number of Level 2 or lower LIGHT Fairy monsters with different names from your Deck to your hand. Add Cyber Petit Angel and Herald of Orange Light. 

  Herald of Perfection is an omni negate and will negate up to the amount of fairy monsters in hand, from this you will get 3 but most likely you will have more in hand adding to the amount of negates. This Combo will change depending on your hand it will end on better if you have the correct cards for example having Megalith Phul on field so that you can go into Megalith Bethor which can be up to three pops or more.  Combo Number Two    If you open Drytron Zeta Aldhibah + Drytron Alpha Thuba (or anything similar it depends on your hand) that is also full combo but a little bit better. One can make I:P Masquerena which can become an Underworld Goddess of the Closed World (when you use up all your negates) which is a kaiju, dark ruler no more, and a negate built into one card or Knightmare Unicorn.   This combo is very similar to the last one, so I am going to speed things up a little       For this combo you need on field Drytron Alpha Thuban, Manju of the Ten Thousand Hands, Megalith Phul, Cyber Angel Idaten. (To get this, Aphla sending Zeta to GY searching Benten then use Zeta effect in GY discard the Benten and serach for Meteonis Drytron and the rest Is just combo number one). On summon Cyber Angel Idaten effect adding Meteonis Drytron. Overlay Megalith Phul and Cyber Angel Idaten for Beatrice, Lady of the Eternal activate effect detach Cyber Angel Idaten, sending Drytron Gamma Eltanin to GY. Activate Meteonis Drytron tributing the Alpha and or Zeta on field to summon Cyber Angel Benten back from GY. Drytron Gamma Eltanin effect in the GY, send Cyber Angel Benten from field to GY to summon itself. Cyber Angel Benten effect in GY searching Herald of Perfection and Gamma effect to summon back a Drytron monster from grave. (You can choose any). Use Meteonis Drytron target Drytron Gamma Eltani to get it back to hand, Now use Meteonis Drytron tribute a Drytron monster (could be any) to summon back from Cyber Angel Idaten, search for Dawn of the Herald. Use Dawn of the Herald tributing Cyber Angel Idate to summon Herald of Perfection. When Dawn and Idate are sent to GY chain link one Idaten, chain link 2 Dawn adding Idaten back to hand. Now using the two extra Drytron monsters to summon anything you want to IP, Verte, or any link 2     Combo Credit to Rampengu Nation  Now these combos will change depending on your hand most of the time for the better, so I encourage you to play around with it. I personally think that Drytron is much more fun now but also much weaker to hand traps. Droll, Forbidden Droplet, Dark Ruler, and cards like those end your turn and break you board just like before.    Any problems with the deck leave them in the comments.  Some spicy Techs in the side deck, Play around with the deck, and List.  Now with all that see you next month because that is seemingly becoming my upload schedule.  Have A Good Day

  3. Increase Tributes Faris

Edit: I must add the new cards otherwise the Archetype will be incomplete

1st turn Deck.. This Deck wants to start with "Revealer" and "Speaker of the Ice Barrier" ("Medallion of Ice Barrier" for Search these Cards &/or "Winds over the Ice Barrier" to special summon) to go into "Bahamut Shark" use its effect and special summon "Toadally Awesome" for free. Maybe you can special summon "Swap Frog" and "Prior of the Ice Barrier" instead to go for "Toadally Awesome" but it would be better if you can do a Synchro summon in the same turn. If you go 2nd you hopefully can go for trishula (wich one you can reach) to break the opponents field. "Trishula Zero Dragon of the Ice Barrier" would be better cause he can directly banish 3 Cards on the field and he specials the original Trishula if he dies. Most people hate to get a monster stolen by Number 101 have fun with this deck ;-) PS: Fury of Kairyu-Shin is inspired by DeathToYourGoose but i liked the Artwork

Main Deck.

Not the best deck, especially since it's being kept as "pure" as possible, with a few exceptions being Elemental HERO Stratos and Vision HERO Vyon, which are excelent searchers and provide good cycling. D-HEROs are exceptionally good at card draw, and because of their broken fusion spell card, Fusion Destiny, you want to cycle fast enough to summon Destiny End Dragoon, which is a complete powerhouse, and with its effect, it will be returning to the field after leaving it because of Fusion Destiny's effect. The deck is pretty self explainatory, and by using Mask Change, you'll disrupt your opponent's handtraps by supponing Masked HERO Dark Law. Everything else is self-explainatory.

Extra Deck.

Xtra HERO Cross Crusader should be used for D-HERO cycling as he can summon D-HEROs from the GY, good targets being Destiny HERO Disk Commander, Destiny HERO Drawguy and Destiny HERO Drilldark, though the timing is important, as the first two's effect is only activated a turn where they weren't sent to the GY. Xtra HERO Wonder Driver can recycle your fusion cards, and Xtra HERO Dread Decimator is a great choice for a finishing turn. Masked HERO Anki  is useful sometimes (and easy to call as most monsters in the deck are DARK), and Masked HERO Dark Law was already discussed.

Ok so. The Fire Kings suck. Arvata is the only decent one because every other fire king either has a ridiculously handcuffed effect that wont make an immediate impact. This is mostly due to the fact that you have to wait until the next standby phase. Now onslaught is also bad because it has far too many restrictions and is actually a genuinely well balanced card. Circle of the Fire Kings could be good as it can cycle stuff with Kitt, but that's really unnecessary and overall almost never going to be impactful enough to warrant the slot.     Now. The synergy is actually pretty good. Arvata destroying Kitt and giving the ability to negate handtraps is very cool and good. Rendezvous and Garunix are awesome for being able to establish tempo and make pushes for lethal. Wolfbark is very cool and good and never a bad card to see in your hand.  You can ABSOLUTELY play the Simorgh + Stormwinds combo because setting up: Simorgh + Statue + Arvata + Rendezvous in grave, is very easy and very strong.  I just wanted to show off something different in my video     See the deck played here: https://youtu.be/twGE88AddR4

deck_excerpt: A D/D/D deck built primarily with a focus on Link Summoning.
deck_description: I never know what to put in these. It's an aggressive combo deck designed to swarm the field with graveyard special summons in order to combo off into the boss monsters and create interruptions. If you're going second, the side deck is covered with ways to out the more common boss monsters that have destruction protection, and also a way to turbo into Kali Yuga, one of the best "going second" boss monsters you can land on imo.  Like any other D/D/D deck, consistency issues can appear once in a while, but in play testing against even the grindiest control decks, I've found ways to survive and end on strong boards.

Its a flip deck that is defensive and tries to out resource you opponent through replacing themselves.  (Note: All of my decks are labeled "Meh" in to help with the understanding that these are not by any means competitive decks. Secondly, all of these decks upon initial completion are untested and purely made by using other decks as reference along with a basic understanding of the archetypes core ideal. Thirdly, All of these decks upon completion are made to be around or below 60$ including shipping, and yes i do use these decks hence why sometimes they are updated to make them better as they get playtested. Fourthly, these decks are generally not a mix of archetypes as its what i prefer. Lastly due to the nature of these decks being non-competitive they do not hold up well to more powerful and expensive cards such as handtraps and cards such as Forbidden Droplet, Evenly Matched, Etc.)

deck_excerpt: Fun deck that revolves around Rekindling and Totem 5 combo for huge OTKs. Lots of Fire monsters and fun combos. Easy to learn for new players and does
deck_description:
Good for both going 1st and 2nd The goal is to set up an OTK with Rekindling summoning 5 monsters from the GY including Totem Five which will wipe the opponent board and inflict tons of damage. Then you can direct attack the opponent for the kill. Other fun combos :
  • Norm Red Resonator, use its effect to spe Firebrand Hymnist, fill up your GY and summon Horse Prince + another monster from the deck (that's the ideal T1 scenario)
  • You have many cards to send to GY cards from your deck (Flamvell Lady, Kirin, Foolish...) your main target is Totem to set up the combo, but if you already have it go for a tuner (Red Resonator or Ashe) instead to have the target for Rekindled Rebirth
  • After using Extravagance you can use Rebirth to summon Sunsaga (Red Resonator + Hazy Flame Cerberus) and destroy cards your opponent controls with its effect (theoretically up to 9 cards but I never managed to get more than 4)
  • Circle of the Fire Kings can trigger the Fire King effects (no s*** Sherlock)
  • If you can't OTK with Rekindling combo, you can still try to summon Crimson Blader to block your opponent's next turn using Rekindling monsters as material
Changes that can be made :
  • 3x Hand Destruction can be too much if your opponent doesn't have 2 or more cards in their hand often
  • Royal Decree can be included against certain decks
  • Any other suggestion you may have, I built this deck for fun in less than an hour and I wasn't familiar with the archetypes so it probably has a lot of room for improvement ! :)
Strenghts : Versatility (OTK, Burn and some defensive options), Stability (there is no real main combo so you're always able to set up an OTK in like 3 turns) and a lot of draw power Weaknesses : Too many to list! This is a fun deck after all Hope you enjoy playing with this deck! :)

Abc without Union Carrier is a sad reality, but like everything in our lives , we have to move on , leaving the past behind.  This list was inspired by the  Editor  Renren when he/she was discursing about possibles ABC combos  in this article . The combo follows this rule , quoute:   "The opening hand is Union Hangar + A piece (A, B, or C) Activate Union Hangar, add B if you didn’t open it, otherwise add A. Normal B, activate Hangar to equip Union Driver to it. Use Driver’s effect to equip C. After that, use C’s effect to summon itself and then go into a generic Link 2. Barricadeborg Blocker "I prefer  I:p Masquerena or  cross-sheep over it,but this depends of your preference" can be cool as it helps SEGOC the effects, but it is optional to do so. Either way, Cl1 C and CL2 B, B adds a second C and C then summons that C you added. Then you go into a generic Link-3 monster, use C’s effect to Special Summon the last piece in your hand which is A-Assault Core! Lastly, link the two away into Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess! Then use A’s effect to recycle back the extra C, and then finally summon ABC! This way you can combat Nibiru way easier, and can still Buster should they Nib on the Link 3 + C." The "new" tech that I implemented was Te Symphonic engine: Symphonic Warrior Guitaar helps to GY set up and summons Symphonic Warrior Miccs ,  a meterial for  Cyber Dragon Infinity and grants you an extra normal summon. Transmodify is a spice tech to trigger  tehe effects of any ABC parts and summons the  Union driver Forbindden Chalice and  Forbidden Lance  are a poor man protection and hand traps, that can be replaced with any  card you desire. Bunjinki Ahsima  is gem of a card, you can use to  go deep in a XYZ line of plays , taking advantage of the fact that all abc parts are level 4, summon Time thief or  Tonado dragon.   This deck, nowadays , is suboptimal that was in the past, however it still is a extreme fun deck to play, being a otk and control in just one deck. I hope you like it.

deck_excerpt: Lock down your opponent and OTK with Dark World and Danger
deck_description: If going first the strategy is to get as much negation on board as possible to lock your opponent down.  Favorite combo play:     Overlay for number 23 using grapha and a danger monster  Activate a danger monster from the hand  Number 23 negates it by dethatching grapha and the danger monster returns to the hand  Summon another level 8 danger monster and summon grapha again  Overlay for Felgrand  Detatch grapha to target itself  Special summon another danger level 8 and grapha one last time  Then overlay for whatever negation xyz is best for your current opponent until you can't anymore or the field is full     If you get multiple grapha and enough danger level 8 monsters, you can do up to 5 overlays in a turn before the field is too full. My favorite lockdown is with these cards:  Number 23  Felgrand  Number 38  Number 90  Evilswarm Nightmare     This board means your opponents first effect of the turn is negated, you can negate 1 spell, you can negate 2 monster effects in two ways, and you can flip two special summoned monsters face down. Also number 38 can redirect attacks to itself, protecting the weaker parts of the lock. This should be difficult for a lot of decks to overcome. You can also sub other monsters for Number 90 and number 38 depending on your opponent, like number 68 or dingirsu. Finally, when you have this lock, you have over 8k attack on board and ready for next turn. If somehow they stop your otk next turn, use your empty XYZ monsters and whatever else you like to summon Aollousa for 4 monster negations on their next turn. If you know they run battle fader or a similar hand trap, summon apollousa and build up the field to otk first. You can negate battle fader, but it returns to the hand. However, you can negate it 4 times with apollousa, ensuring your OTK will land.     If going second, summon removal if needed, or just do the lock down play to OTK. Favorite play going second is:  Dingirsu to remove a backrow  Pain gainer to clear front row (Summon a second rank 8 first if needed to boost the def for the effect)  Seven Sins to beat down and remove next turn if needed  Then keep summoning until I can OTK

deck_excerpt: An optimised Ancient Gear Train deck. It's a really fun deck with a lot of options.
deck_description: I made 2 previous versions but realised the deck lacked something. I switched around some cards and put some backrow removal and kaijus in it. This deck has 2 goals. Summoning high level xyz with the trains, the Flying Pegasus and the Anchor Drill. And getting your Chaos Ancient Gear Giant out. Ancient Gears on their own are not that good in my opinion so a little support from an archetype that can frequently summon is nice.   Monsters Ancient Gear Golem: You don't really want to draw this card. You can't special summon it and tribute summoning this thing gets countered very easily which ends up with you losing 2 or three cards (if geartown is on the field only 2). It's why I put them at 1. I don't think you will even use more than 1 Golems in a duel. The longer the duel lasts the harder it becomes to win. Ancient Gear Gadjiltron Dragon: I can hear you thinking to yourself; "Why Gadjiltron Dragon? Ancient Gear Reactor Dragon is much better!!" True the card is better, but for what we are trying to do here Gadjiltron Dragon suits this deck better with it 8 star scaling. With this card you can get very easily into Seven Sins and banish your oponnent's monsters often locking them out of their effects in the process. This card is searchable with Urgent Schedule, Ancient Gear Wyvern and can be returned from the graveyard using Bullet Express Train. So only 2 as well. Ancient Gear Wyvern: This card is basically the Elemental Hero Stratos of this deck. It searches out any Ancient Gear cards in your deck. You can extend the combo searching for Ancient Gear Box first and then using the effect of Box you can add an Ancient Gear Frame or Infinitrack Anchordrill to your hand. You go plus 2 for no cost so run three at all times. Ancient Gear Box: This the garnet in the deck so you really don't want to draw it. I run the card at one because it is recyclable so you can just use it from the graveyard again. Running at 2 could be possible too but I would not recommend it at three. The risk of drawing it increases substantially. Ancient Gear Hunting Hound: A walking polymerization. When summoned it does 600 damage to your opponent but We use it for its ability to fusion summon any Ancient Gear monster. Often we fuse into Ancient Gear Howitzer to get an Ancient Gear Golem on the field. Use 2 or 3 Ancient Gear Howitzer: In my opinion a very underrated card. Unaffected by card effects and it can inflict 1000 damage to your opponent... Every turn. Your opponent probably wants this card destroyed. But if for some reason he doesn’t and you don’t really care for the burn effect you can always destroy it yourself to get Ancient Gear Golem out to fusion summon a Chaos Ancient Gear Giant. If you have Ancient Gear Golem out in the field and you use Ancient Gear Fusion you can use material from the deck to complete the summon instead. So Howitzer is a powerful card that opens the path to an even better card. We run 1 or 2. Super Express Bullet Train: A rank 10 train card that is very easy to bring out. All you need, is to have only earth machine monsters on the field. Usually the plan is to bring out this card together with Heavy Freight Train Derricane and possible Flying Pegasus and Anchordrill to xyz summon your bossmonsters. Downside is that it can’t attack without sending 2 cards you control to the graveyard. This however poses no problem for us because we only use it as xyz fodder. A nice extra is that it lets you take back a card from the graveyard to your hand if Bullet train is in the graveyard that turn. I run 2. I wouldn’t use three to prevent bricking. Infinitrack Anchordrill: Has enormous synergy with the Ancient Gear archetype. It is usable for Ancient Gear Box because it has 500ATK and it can summon another card from the hand. Besides that it can combine the stars for both cards making lets say Gadjiltron Dragon and Anchordrill fodder for the rank 12 xyz Seven Sins. Heavy Freight Train Derricane: Just like Bullet Express Train it is so easy to bring out. Use this card for xyz fodder too. Ideally we run 2. Flying Pegasus Railroad Stampede: Lets you summon a card from your graveyard in defense position but without its effect. Nice effect but we will use its secondary one more often. It lets us copy the level of another face up card to either Flying pegasus or the other way around. Best used with the trains or level 8 monsters. I use 3. Gameciel, The Sea Turtle Kaiju: When testing this deck online, I often see cards like Red Eyes Dark Dragoon or other cards with negates and protection. For now it is in the main deck. But if it is not to your liking you can always change it for an extra Hunting Hound, AG Fusion or Exodius the Ultimate Forbidden Lord. Machina Citadel: we use it as xyz fodder and sometimes you can use its effect to destroy your opponent's monsters. One is enough.   Spells/Traps Ancient Gear Catapult: We use Catapult to pop Geartown and summon Ancient Gear golem and Wyvern to get into Chaos Giant. Only way to really summon Golem aside from tributing and using Howitzer. Run three at all times, it is the foundation of the Ancient Gears. Geartown: Used in tandem with Catapult this can give you a Chaos Giant and more. Like Catapult, run three at all times. Ancient Gear Fusion: If used with Ancient Gear Golem you can search the deck for materials too. Chaos Giant can be out in one turn this way. I would runtwo or three. Urgent Schedule: This card lets you summon 2 monsters from the deck. One lvl four or lower and one level five or higher. This used to be quite an expensive card but is more affordable nowadays. Getting 2 free summons when your opponent controls more cards is very helpful for your xyz and fusion plays. I recommend running 3. Harpie's Feather Duster: Good for backrow removal but limited, so one. Twin Twisters: Good for backrow removal and to pop Geartown. also one. Solemn Strike: Just nice to negate an effect or special summon. Run one. Solemn Judgement: To negate cards that would otherwise break your board. Run one. Unending Nightmare: Nice for backrow removal and to pop your own cards like Geartown. we use 2.   The extra deck Double Headed Anger Knuckle: This card is good for getting those level 10 cards on the field. We use only one. Ancient Gear Ballista: This card is a godsend for Ancient Gear players. It synergizes immensely with the trains and earth machine monsters in general. It only requires 2 earth machine monsters to summon it. Ballista can add one Geartown to your hand or any Ancient Gear Monster in the main deck. Usually what you want to do with this card is to add a Geartown to your hand, you play it and then activate Ballista’s secondary effect to reduce an opponent’s monster ATK/DEF to zero and send the Geartown to the graveyard as cost which in turn activates Geartown’s effect. Chaos Ancient Gear Giant: The one card I’ve been talking about so much. With his 4500 atk and powerful effect it’s a force to be reckoned with. Unaffected by spell and trap cards and the option to attack every monster your opponent controls once. If that wasn’t good enough already it does piercing damage too. Run 1 or 2, it depends really. Ultimate Ancient Gear Golem: Sporting an attack of 4400 this card this card is quite the powerhouse too. Its effect isn’t as good as Chaos Giant but it can get an Ancient Gear Golem on the field when destroyed, giving you the chance to get another Chaos Giant. We run 1 or 2. Megaton Ancient Gear Golem: Essentially a weaker version of Chaos Ancient Gear Giant. When fusion summoned with more than one Ancient Gear Golem it can attack multiple times in your battle phase. When destroyed by card effect you can get your Ultimate Golem out and that way you could get an Chaos Ancient Gear Giant too. Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Juggernaut Liebe: A rank 11 xyz easily summoned using Number 81: Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Super Dora. Can attack up to the number of attached materials plus one. You can boost the attack of this card by 2000 by detaching one card which makes Liebe a powerful beatstick. 1 is more than enough. Number 81: Superdreadnought Rail Cannon Super Dora: Can detach one card to make another unaffected by card effects. When used on Chaos Giant it makes the card nearly invincible. Number 77 Seven Sins: Out of all the rank 12 cards this one is the easiest to summon. There are 3 ways to summon it and they all have their merits.. We can summon it the normal way by using 2 rank 12 monsters, this has the advantage that we can use its effect immediately and banish your opponent monsters. The only downside here is that seven sins has only 1 card to protect itself when targeted for battle or by card effects unless you don’t activate the effect. The second way involves xyz summuning Rank 8 Dingirsu Orcust of The Evening Star to your field. You then overlay Pain Gainer on it and then into Seven Sins. Last way to summon it is to xyz summon Ravenous Tarantula into Sevens Sins or first into Pain Gainer and then Seven Sins. We run only one, the resources needed for this card are substantial enough that you probably won’t get another one on the field. Number 84 Pain Gainer: Also 2 ways of summoning it but doing it the normal way  is not really possible in this deck. We mostly use Dingirsu or Ravenous Tarantula to summon it instead. Usually this card is just a stepping stone for Seven Sins or if you can summon Seven Sins the normal way and still have room for Pain Gainer it can be a good card on its own. We Also run one. Number 35 Ravenous Tarantula: If used a bit further down the duel this card will turn all your monsters into beatsticks on steroids. It adds the difference in life points as attack and defense to face up cards you control. This in combination with a Chaos Giant will completely destroy any monster. We mostly use the rank 10 trains or a Flying Pegasus to Xyz into it. If you decide to not go further the xyz chain and keep it as it is you can punish special summoning with it too. Every time your opponent special summons a monster they lose 600 lifepoints. And if that wasn’t enough you can detach one monster to destroy all monsters your opponent controls that have attack less or equal to this card. You could run 2 but I run one. Dingirsu The Orcust of The Evening Star: Really a good staple as well. I am actually inclined to use Dingirsu more then Harbinger in duels. You can use this card for Pain Gainer too. Aside from that it can protect cards from destruction by detaching materials. Run 2. Number 27: Dreadnought Dreadnoid: Can be used as material for Dora when you destroy a monster by battle. It has build in protection as well. I would run 1, it’s a good card but I don’t use it all that often. There is no side deck in this profile. I leave this to your imagination.

deck_excerpt: Shaddoll-Invoked deck to play in the Switch Game Legacy of the Duelist - Link Evolution
deck_description: You may have fogotten this deck, but it's somehow back in the meta of March 2021, let that deck do it's thing.  The main objective of this deck is to get El Shaddoll Winda and Invoked Mechaba on the field. However, it can manage to build an oppresive board (by March 2020 standards) by summoning El Shaddoll Winda and El Shaddoll Construct if you are unable to draw any Invoked engine cards.  If only Shaddoll Schism was in this game...  PSY-Frame package is here for light fodder and also if you happen to be in the position of summoning PSY-Framelord Lambda, which can help you to negate those monsters which you will prefer not banish (or discard) for Mechaba's effect.  Don't forget to summon Cross-Sheep!  Remember this deck is for the Switch game, this deck lacks the current consistency and power that Dogmatika cards boost to this deck, this deck tries to get the best out of what is available in this game's card pool and banlist.

deck_excerpt: Synchro Summoning, and lots of it. Feedback is very welcome!
deck_description: Synchro Summon, draw a bunch of cards, Synchro Summon some more, and repeat until you can't anymore. Tatsunoko and Tin Musical Battlemech are pretty interchangeable here. If you have Junk Converter in your hand, you use its effect to discard itself and a tuner to search Junk Synchron (if it's already in your hand, search Synchron Carrier instead) and summon said Junk Synchron to revive Converter. Synchro summon Junk Speeder with them (if you have Carrier on the field, summon Hyper Librarian instead and follow up by using Converter to revive your synchron and summon Speeder with it and Carrier, either way you want HL on the field) and summon Cyberse Synchron (preferably) and some others like Steam Synchron. Basically just keep Synchro Summoning until you run out of gas. WARNING: This Deck plays like an automobile. It's really easy to get momentum going, but when you lose that momentum, it's very noticeable. This deck's gas is the Tuners. What's a Synchron Deck without Stardust Dragon?

deck_excerpt: Crazy Blue-Eyes - Invoked deck that works in Legacy of the Duelist - Link Evolution
deck_description:
This is the deck of a madman. But it works, at least in Link Evolution game's format. This crazy deck works, here are some things this deck can do:
  • Summon Invoked Mechaba ASAP
  • Use multiple Special summon like Chaos Dragons, Blue-Eyes Alternative, CED or Danger! cards as fodder for Apollousa, Cross-Sheep or BLS.
  • Use Danger! cards to dig through your deck in order to find any Invoked engine card, while also providing Level 7+ fodder for BLS - Soldier of Chaos or Apollousa.
  • Turbo out three of the best (in my opinion) Rank 8 monsters.
  • If the timing is right, you can special summon Purgatrio, trample your opponent monsters, and then, use a Stone to summon Borreload Savage.
Don't forget to set your Invocation before use Danger! effect from your hand. Remember, this deck is meant to be played in the switch game. When in-person events are back, I will try a more modern version of this deck, with Chaos Space, Noctovision Dragon, Parallel eXCeed and some other newer cards.

deck_excerpt: Crazy Invoked - Blue-Eyes deck that works in Legacy of the Duelist - Link Evolution
deck_description:
This is the deck of a madman. But it works, at least in Link Evolution game's format. This crazy deck works, here are some things this deck can do:
  • Summon Invoked Mechaba ASAP
  • Use multiple Special summon like Chaos Dragons, Blue-Eyes Alternative, CED or Danger! cards as fodder for Apollousa, Cross-Sheep or Black Luster Soldier - Soldier of Chaos, which is almost a win condition in this game.
  • Use Danger! cards to dig through your deck in order to find any Invoked engine card, while also providing Level 7+ fodder for BLS - Soldier of Chaos or Apollousa.

Remember, this deck is meant to be played in the switch game. When in-person events are back, I will try a more modern version of this deck, with Chaos Space, Noctovision Dragon, Parallel eXCeed and some other newer cards.

deck_excerpt: Dragons come at the roar of the Phantasmal Lord. Get ready for its wrath! :3 Los dragones acuden al rugir del Señor Fantasmal. Prepárense para su ira
deck_description:
Deck creado por: Darklab Objetivo: Invocar a Ultimitl Bishbaalkin usando a los Dragon Link, enviarlo al campo oponente y quemar su vida con Machu Mech :3 Link a la demostración del Deck: >>>>> https://youtu.be/IefsEAtd5-Y <<<< Requisitos para iniciar el combo: Al final se necesitará varios dragones, pero éstos son fáciles de spamear en la baraja. Siempre la idea es ir por Romulus y los Guardragon para acceder a sus efectos de spam y tener en campo a Spiral Dragon, junto a un tuner y un no tuner. Extenders para iniciar el combo:
  • Absorouter Dragon: Se invoca solo si controlamos un Rokket, lo cual es sencillo. Aún así, siempre se puede enviar al cementerio para añadirnos un Rokket a la mano.
  • Noctovision Dragon: Se invoca solo si invocamos otro dragón de modo especial. Además, cuando se va del campo, nos da un robo!
  • Black Dragon Collapserpent: Se invoca gratis removiendo un monstruo de luz, además nos trae a Wyverburster.
  • White Dragon Wyverburster: Se invoca gratis removiendo un monstruo de oscuridad, además nos trae a Collapserpent.
  • Supreme King Dragon Darkwurm: Se invoca gratis del cementerio, por lo que es el target preferido de Foolish Burial y Dragon Shrine.
  • Starliege Dragon Seyfert: Una invocación normal excelente, ya que con su efecto tendremos en mano a Collapserpent o Wyverburster.
  • Rokket Tracer: Normal Summon de último recurso, además de tener excelentes interacciones con Section Boot y Absorouter. Y es tuner!
  • Black Metal Dragon: Excelente Normal Summon. Nos añade al Red Eyes Darkness Metal Dragon, que es un +1.
  • One For One: Nos trae a Black Metal Dragon.
  • Dragon Shrine y Foolish Burial: Ver Darkwurm.
  • Monster Reborn: Nos da un cuerpo adicional.
  • Chaos Space: Efecto similar a Seyfert, pero sin gastar la Normal Summon.
  • Quick Revolve: Nos trae a Rokket Tracer gratis.
  • Guardragon of the World Legacy: Efecto similar a Monster Reborn, pero además nos permite mover a un dragón (por lo general un Guardragon).
Pros:
  • Deck bastante consistente.
  • El deck no tiene garnets, ya que Phalanx no es necesario para completar el combo.
  • El deck tiene extenders muy poderosos, por lo que es posible que sobren recursos en mano.
  • El deck no depende de una única forma de invocar a Bishbaalkin, por lo que la primera mitad del combo es muy flexible.
  • Puede baitear hantraps con los extenders suficientes.
  • Versátil. Es fácil adaptarse a distintos recursos en mano.
Contras:
  • El deck depende del Spiral Dragon, por lo que si no podemos acceder a él o su efecto es negado, será gg.
  • Por la naturaleza del deck, éste no tiene acceso a protección.
  • El deck es susceptible a Nibiru, Called by the grave y Ghost Belle, al igual que a Veiler e Impermanence si los usan correctamente.
  • El deck depende del burn, por lo que es susceptible a cartas que aumenten los LP del oponente.

deck_name: Chaos Thunder Dragon 60 Cards - Combos + Test Hands
deck_description:
Hello and welcome to my Chaos Thunder dragon deck!! Thunder Dragons have always been a favorite of mine (after dragon link of course!) and it is very unfortunate that Colossus is STILL on the banlist (WHY KONAMI WHY??). I also noticed that I have not uploaded a single thunder dragon deck on this site and a bunch of people have been requesting this build. For these reasons, I have decided to upload one!! This deck is a full 60 deck and I would give it a solid rogue tier in the current metagame. It won’t win an LCS or anything but it is a very fun deck to play and I guarantee you that you can even win duels sometimes. I have once again gone all out on a deck explanation (sigh, this is 60 cards) so I really hope you enjoy it!!   Just a quick reminder that the deck explanation, All the combos, test hands, deck explanations and ways to best use your resources are ALL on my Youtube video. Subscribing to the channel would be a great way to support me and the channel!   Link to the video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bQnrpwVoLAw   Deck Ratios -    Note: some cards may be in more than 1 category   
Thunder Dragon engine - Thunder Dragon cards and cards in the deck that support them  For this engine we have 3 Vanilla Thunder Dragon, 3 dragondark, 3 Dragonroar, 2 dragonmatrix, 1 dragonhawk, 1 fusion and 1 Gold Sarcophagus. We are not playing lupine or solar since this is not a pure build, it also involves a lot of other engines. Fusion is usually a 2 of but we are only running 1 because we only need 1 titan, same reason as for not playing solar and lupine. Dragondark is the best thunder dragon in my opinion since it searches and Dragonroar is good because it gives you access to dragondark and dragonmatrix. The vanilla is played for extra pops with titan and for graveyard and card advantage. Matrix is a solid card which also adds to the pops. Notice all the thunders can be recycled with fusion and The chaos creator. Fusion is usually not a card you want to draw, it is one that you mill using verte (the reason we only play 1 copy). Sarcophagus is great since it can banish any thunder directly from the deck to trigger it’s banish effect. Hawk is just a great searchable extender and can be used to bring back titan from the grave as well (if needed). That is basically all for the thunder engine, who’s main purpose is to generate card and graveyard advantage and turbo titan. 
Chaos engine - cards that can be search with chaos space basically Oh my god we have a lot of stuff for this! Here we go - 3 Valkaria, 2 lavineer, 1 black dragon, 1 white dragon, 2 emperor, 3 creator and 3 chaos space. Chaos space can search any of these so it is a really good card to open. It can also recycle and generate SOOO much card advantage. Valkaria and the baby chaos dragons are your best chaos monsters (to draw) because they only require 1 light or dark in the grave, they are level 4 and because they generate some sort of advantage (the baby chaos dragons search each other and Valkaria can mill when banished). Lavineer is also amazing since it can be used to hand rip OR pop 2 cards on the field OR even monster reborn a monster from the grave!! It also requires 3 banishes which can be useful if you have multiple thunders in the GY. Emperor can recycle any of your banished dragons by destroying itself (this puts it in your extra deck), and then it can be summoned from the extra deck by banishing a light and dark from the grave and can also clear the field if needed. It generates a lot of advantage especially since both effects will be used to the fullest. Creator is also making since it can special back from the banish zone (thunders!!) and recycle which is really really good and is the reason I am maxing out on this. The main reason this in in the deck is to swarm the field, go into rank 8 plays and link plays, and to banish the thunders in the graveyard to generate all sorts of advantage. 
Lightsworn engine - cards that search raiden and mill basically We have 3 charge and 2 raiden. Charge is the best opener since charge + level 4 extender = mill 9 + chaos ruler + search a light or dark (see combos in video for more info and how to achive that). Raiden is just a 2 of, great tuner as well. Main reason this in in the build is because raiden is your main normal summon (alongside tracer) and because you need to mill cards to generate advantage. 
Rokket engine - cards that support the rokket archetype  The rokket engine is - 3 quick launch, 3 rokket tracer, 1 rokket recharger and 1 boot sector launch. The main reason this is even in the deck is to turbo out chaos ruler from the extra deck. Very self explanatory and can also be used to go into romulus and fetch a ravine if you have another dragon out. Rokkets are a solid and splashable engine. 
Pendulum dragon engine - You will NEVER actually pendulum summon but this is basically good dragons that can be searched using revolution dragon.  For this engine we have 3 Revolution, 2 emperor and 1 darkwurm. Revolution can search both emperor and darkwurm since they are pendulum dragons and can also reborn something like hope harbinger from the grave (does not require materials to negate). Revolution is just such an amazing draw and it also serves as an additional body in the GY if you use it’s discard effect. Emperor is just SOOOOO good!! It recycles any of your banished dragons by destroying itself (this puts it in your extra deck), and then it can be summoned from the extra deck by banishing a light and dark from the grave and can also clear the field if needed (also level 8)! What a card!! Darkwurm is good because it is a free special summon and is just a solid pick in general. It is really good if opened with ravine and can also be milled with ravine. The main purpose of this engine is to generate advantage and swarm the field. 
Danger! Engine - literally danger cards We have - 3 mothman, 1 Nessie, 1 jack and 1 thunderbird. These ratios might sound weird to you but there is a specific reason these are the ones I chose. I chose ones that generate some kind of card/grave advantage if discarded (except thunderbird which is there just to summon off of jack). Moth is also a level 4 which synergies with the rokket and lightsworn engine (to turbo out ruler) and it can also be linked off or used to summon Douglass which generates more card/grave advantage. No snake because if discard it brings itself back, which is good but it does not put a danger in the grave (all the others that have good discard effects stay in the grave as chaos banish targets). Dangers main purpose in this is to spam monsters, go for rank 4 palys, dig deeper into the deck, draw cards and to help get stuff into the grave. 
Dragon Ravine Engine - cards that go with Dragon ravine We have - 3 Dragon Ravines, 1 terraforming, 1 foolish burial, 1 black wing elite, 1 galactic spiral and 1 seyfert. We are playing maximum ravines because we will not always have access to it and because the card is literally fire. Opening multiple copies is also AMAZING! Keep in mind that ravine is not a hard once per turn so the blackwing can bounce ravine to summon itself and then you can use ravine again! Sadly the blackwing is once per duel :( foolish burial can mill anything in the entire deck so why not run it? Seyfert and Spiral are mill targets for ravine to recycle and go into rank 8 plays respectively. We are not running seyfert as a normal summon to search the baby chaos dragons because we cannot afford to waste our normal summon on it. If opened, it should (in most cases) just be discarded. Ravine is definitely a 3 of, you cannot cut down on it. This idea of playing 3 ravines I stole from Jesse Kotton, so credits to him :)
  Extra deck cards -    All of these cards are 1 of btw.   
Thunder Dragon Titan Thunder dragon’s boss monster that can cause interruption during opponent’s turn, 1 is more than enough. (Rip Colossus)
Chaos Ruler The best card in the entire extra deck, is a +1 and also mills 4 cards and can also come back from the grave for more advantage!!
Borreload savage  Omni negate, a card you can make sometimes if you draw an extra quick launch
Striker Dragon Link 1 for rokket and baby chaos dragon combos. Can be recycled so just 1 copy.
Seals You can make this if you open the baby chaos dragons, amazing interruption during opponent’s turn. 
Romulus Searches ravine - all you need to know.
Verte You summon Titan using this
I:P Great to make unicorn/Phoenix during an opponent's turn or for even making apollusa during an opponent's turn if dark locked or if you used verte. 
Pheonix Backrow removal
Unicorn High Impact Removal 
Apollusa Negates monster effects and can be made with I:P 
Accesscode Otk and removal card
Douglass For those times when you have 2 level 4 monsters but no tuners. It can draw 2 and make you discard 1, great card and graveyard advantage. 
Hope harbinger  Spell Negate and can be monster reborned with revolution dragon (does not need materials to negate)
Lancelot GREAT card!! It is literally sooo good! It can pop (only useful if going 2nd) and can also serve as an Omni negate during an opponent's turn. Best of all it is dark, meaning you can summon it even if you are tracer locked. 
  Jesus Christ it took forever to type all that up but alas I am done! I really hope you enjoy the deck explanation and I recommend you try this deck out.    Again, deck explanation, All the combos, test hands, deck explanations and ways to best use your resources are ALL on my Youtube video. Also make sure to answer the poll question down below!   Link to the video - https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=bQnrpwVoLAw   Thanks, and I will see you next time!! :)

Electrumite didn't get unbanned, but pends are still the best deck. Isolde is an alternative that provides great card advantage, especially because you can still use the warrior you search in the pendulum zone. This deck has 4 main starts to the combo.
  1. Use deep sea diva to summon neptabyss and spam goyo defender. Make isolde and search an igknight, then dump cursed bamboo sword and summon renaud to draw 2 cards. From there you can make apollousa and then conduct a giant pendulum summon.
  2. Use righty driver to make goyo defender. This is the same as the first start, but you don't get the benefits of deep sea minstrel and lappis dragon later in the combo.
  3. Just use any tuner and another monster to make halqifibrax. This is not the ideal combo but can still make 2 negates on its own.
  4. Use any two warriors to make isolde. You can use igknights to search red layer if you need to. This start is not the best but it can still set up the pendulum summon and get you some draws of the bamboo swords.
At the end of combo you can use your pendulum scales to search gearfried for an extra negate.

deck_excerpt: Main deck is a Numeron Kaiju engine. In order to counter your opponents side deck swap, toss in your whole side deck which is a Mystic Mine burn engin
deck_description: SO, this is by far my favorite deck. Even with ZEXAL banned Numerons still work very well. It's just a matter of how you do it. The main deck is a Numeron Kaiju engine. If you can get Numeron Network, and your opponent has 1 or 2 monsters it is an OTK. Replace a monster with a kaiju (or both with lava). One other note, is if you can USE THE KAIJUS ON DRAGOON. It is by far the best counter, and you need to do it before you use Numeron Networks effect because you can only summon 1 monster after you use it's effect. All the hand traps are for interrupting, and then you have all of the searches. Interdimentional Matter Transport isn't a good card, normally, BUT in this deck if I clear my Infinitrack or Mekk knight, I can activate my Numeron Network.  Extra Deck: All the Numeron monsters work off of Calling/Network, Infinitrack and Mekk knight are to clear off your Numerons so you don't have to have an empty board. Linkuriboh is there to counter tokens and to drop off your extra Numeron XYZ monster.  Side deck: This is when the whole deck gets fun, toss your whole extra deck into the main deck and drop the following cards from your main deck: Numeron Wall (3), Numeron Network (3), Numeron Calling (3), Memories of Hope (2), Interrupting Kaiju Slumber (2), and Interdimensional Matter Transport (2). Now your deck is a Mystic Mine burn deck.  As cheesy as this deck is, it works very very well and can counter cards like Nibiru, which your opponite will add after the first round. I do believe that this deck can be used in a competitive format. Let me know what you think of this deck!  ~Lt. Banger

deck_description: Decided to edit the Mechanized Mayhem structure deck with cards from some of the recent packs. Feel free to feedback below
https://youtu.be/crfK2B0gD0E

Okay, for this strategy, it's a blinding 2nd deck. It's not very strong going 1st although you can get some okay boards going and at least a negate. I added Dangers and Performages just to give the deck a bit of a splash and to summon generic extra deck stuff easier (note: all of the Plunder ships are generic to summon except for Blackbeard). I got the idea of splashing some of these monsters from my previous deck which functions similarly as they both are discard heavy. How I play this deck is very aggressive, and the main idea is to break boards (hence the Kaiju package). The Knightmares are staples, and they benefit from Brann's ATK boost. Most Plunder decks use Bahamut and Toad, but I use it mostly as a backup. Dragite is kinda the star in ways since it's very easy to summon, and you have access to an easy negate. My favorite card in here is Draco Berserker because it's an OTK enabler and disruptor. The easiest way to understand this deck is to try and summon as much as you can to go into the ships to banish or negate monsters and to gain tremendous ATK boosts for an OTK. This deck going 2nd works extremely well, and you have options to summon a few different monsters other than Plunders. However, some of the Plunder monsters may lock you into only summoning their archetype, but it's not that big of a problem. Just note to always equip the Plunders to their ships if you can. The deck is a bit fast and you might accidentally drop your hand while building a board. Another thing is to try learning every Plunders' full effects. They do a couple of different things. I hope this deck helps some of you guys out if you are looking into building this. Feel free to ask any questions too.

Standard Gladiator Beast deck. Uses the same strategies as in 2012, so have fun playing it.

Overview

For those new in the archetype, your job is to have your Gladiator Beasts fight and survive those figthts. During the end of the Battle Phase (any player's), you can return them to the deck and Special Summon another Gladiator Beast monster with a different name (hereafter refered as tag-out) to activate their effects, which are triggered when they are Special Summoned by the effect of a Gladiator Beast monster. Furthermore, by returning to the deck, you can Fusion Summon (hereafter refered as contact fusion or simply contact) several strong monsters that can also tag-out). In order to tag-out, you need to survive fights, which wou will be able to do with some support, cards like Effect Veiler, Gladiator Beast Vespasius, Gladiator Beast Heraklinos, Gladiator Beast Domitianus, Shrink, and Book of Moon will aid in prevention of effects, manipulating battle positions and increasing-decreasing Attack stats to have your beasts fight and survive, and even if you are to take Battle Damage, you'll get in return field control as will be discussed below.

The Combatants

Effect Veiler: Not a beast, but a great hand trap that aids in prevention of your main monsters' destruction by battle. She can be swapped with any of the other hand traps in the Side Deck, depending on your needs. Gladiator Beast Attorix: Her main use will be to send Gladiator Beast Bestiary to the GY to contact for Gladiator Beast Gyzarus, although due to her effect changing her level, you could send a level 5 or higher Gladial to contact Gladiator Beast Tamer Editor. Gladiator Beast Augustus: This beatstick has a good attack stat (above 2500 which helps against a lot of common threats), but his primary use will be to Special Summon a level 5 or higher Gladiator Beast from your hand to contact summon Gladiator Beast Tamer Editor, or Gladiator Beast Bestiary, Gladiator Beast Laquari, or simply contact Gladiator Beast Andabata. You could also Link Summon Gladiator Beast Dragases or Test Panther if in need of more board options. Gladiator Beast Bestiary: One of the most important Gladials in the archetype, for both its ability to clear enemy backrow, and to contact summon Gladiator Beast Gyzarus. You could run 3 copies, though I feel you can recycle them easily enough via Gladiator Beast Darius, Gladiator Beast Equeste, and Gladiator Beast's Comeback. Gladiator Beast Darius: This guy's job is to revive his teammates to swarm the board, or simply to contact an useful Summon. Because he negates their effects, brought-back monsters won't activate their effects, but still helps in cycling strategies. Gladiator Beast Equeste: Another recycle card. This one is useful because it targets a Gladiator Beast card, so you can bring to hand spells and traps, namely, Gladiator Beast War Chariot, which is a strong defensive option. Gladiator Beast Laquari: Laquari's there to establish an ofensive board, bringing 2100 Attack when Summoned by another Gladiator Beast, and serving as main contact material for Gladiator Beast Heraklinos. Gladiator Beast Murmillo: This fish is a destroy option, being the counterpart to Bestiary. However, he is slightly weaker due to reduced stats. Gladiator Beast Noxious: This beast is a great defensive option, and depending on how you play him, you can establish board during your opponent's turn, by allowing a clean board to spam beasts, depending on how or what you bring: for example, Gladiator Beast Darius helps with an early contact next turn, Gladiator Beast Sagittarii for card cycling, Gladiator Beast Augustus for readying a play next turn by returning a monster to your deck, etc. Gladiator Beast Retiari: GY removal tool. Simple yet so useful. Gladiator Beast Sagittarii: Strong draw option, which the deck can get some help with. Also establishes GY that can be used with Gladiator Beast Darius for easy contact or Link. Gladiator Beast Vespasius: A great ofensive option, Special Summoning himself from the hand when battling, granting 500 Attack to all your monsters, which will surprise your opponent. He also contacts Gladiator Beast Domitianus, if you need to do so. Test Tiger: Not a Gladiator Beast, but a really strong support. Its effect is to bring another monster and activate their effects due to tag-out. Summons itself, so you can also Link with him, though simply tagging is more efficient most of the time.

The Tools of Battle

Spells are pretty straightforward in this deck, Gladiator Beasts's Comeback is a revival/summoning tool from hand or GY for tag-out, Link or contact fusion, Gladiator Proving Ground is a search option/deck thinner, Gladiator Rejection is an interesting defensive/ofensive tool, Gladiator Beast's Respite is strong card draw, Raigeki and Harpie's Feather Duster are just self-explainatory, and Shrink is a powerful and unexpected removal tool that has great synergy with this deck. On traps, you won't use that many, being an aggresive deck, there's no time for waiting. Defensive Tactics prevents destruction and allows to go all-in without taking battle damage, plus it self-cycles to the deck, and Gladiator Beast War Chariot prevents handtraps, several monster effects and disrupts a great deal of monsters, as it does not target.

The New Challengers

Gladiator Beast Andabata: Its main use lies in its attack stat, and summoning Gladiator Beast Gyzarus easily enough (being the only Level 7 or lower in the Extra Deck). Gladiator Beast Domitianus: Great defensive tool with monster effect denial. Also has great presence due to its high stats, and can be brought with ease. Have fun. Gladiator Beast Gyzarus: One of the best contacts since early stages of Gladiator Beast's life as a deck. Destroying up to two cards is just too strong, and bringing two gladiators when tagging-out is just too good. He is also Summoned way too easy, having several options to bring him in. Gladiator Beast Heraklinos: His greatest strength lies in both high stats and good effect that is not activated once per turn, though costs a card to be discarted. He also cannot tag-out, which limits his versatility, but bringing both him and Gladiator Beast Domitianus will be a big enough board to have your opponent think as their options will be thinner. Gladiator Beast Nerokius: Nerokius has an ancient gear-like effect, so tagging with him will be easier, as he has a strong Attack stat, and by doing so, you'll bring another two monsters to control the board even easier. Gladiator Beast Tamer Editor: A big powerhouse of the deck, which is one of the newest and strongest fusions, as its effect of Special Summoning fusion monsters from the Extra Deck will aid in a lot of control, bringing in Gladiator Beast Heraklinos for spell/trap negation,  Gladiator Beast Domitianus for effect denial, or maybe Gladiator Beast Gyzarus for destruction. Simply great to have. Apollousa, Bow of the Goddess: Great monster for swarming decks, and this is one of those. Effect denial and big attack is something you want when using this deck. Gladiator Beast Dragases: Prevents effects with an Ancient Gear-like effect, plus destruction by battle denial on your attacking monsters. He won't last long on the field, as tagging-out will bring two companions, so that effect should be used fully. Test Panther: A stronger Test Tiger, as it won't tribute itself, and on Link Summoning will give you hand to toy with, best when used with a current Gladiator Beast on your field, as you can bring Gladiator Beast Vespasius or Gladiator Beast Noxius to your hand, then tagging-out into Gladiator Beast Augustus so you can Special summon one of the former, so you can quickly contact into Gladiator Beast Tamer Editor.
